2420 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
2421 
2422 static MemberDef *addVariableToFile(
2423  EntryNav *rootNav,
2424  MemberType mtype,
2425  const QCString &scope,
2426  const QCString &name,
2427  bool fromAnnScope,
2428  /*int indentDepth,*/
2429  MemberDef *fromAnnMemb)
2430 {
2431  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
2432  Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0,
2433  " global variable:\n"
2434  " type=`%s' scope=`%s' name=`%s' args=`%s' prot=`%d mtype=%d lang=%d\n",
2435  qPrint(root->type),
2436  qPrint(scope),
2437  qPrint(name),
2438  qPrint(root->args),
2439  root->protection,
2440  mtype,
2441  root->lang
2442  );
2443 
2444  FileDef *fd = rootNav->fileDef();
2445 
2446  // see if we have a typedef that should hide a struct or union
2447  if (mtype==MemberType_Typedef && Config_getBool(TYPEDEF_HIDES_STRUCT))
2448  {
2449  QCString type = root->type;
2450  type.stripPrefix("typedef ");
2451  if (type.left(7)=="struct " || type.left(6)=="union ")
2452  {
2453  type.stripPrefix("struct ");
2454  type.stripPrefix("union ");
2455  static QRegExp re("[a-z_A-Z][a-z_A-Z0-9]*");
2456  int l,s;
2457  s = re.match(type,0,&l);
2458  if (s>=0)
2459  {
2460  QCString typeValue = type.mid(s,l);
2461  ClassDef *cd = getClass(typeValue);
2462  if (cd)
2463  {
2464  // this typedef should hide compound name cd, so we
2465  // change the name that is displayed from cd.
2466  cd->setClassName(name);
2467  cd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
2468  cd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
2469  return 0;
2470  }
2471  }
2472  }
2473  }
2474 
2475  // see if the function is inside a namespace
2476  NamespaceDef *nd = 0;
2477  if (!scope.isEmpty())
2478  {
2479  if (scope.find('@')!=-1) return 0; // anonymous scope!
2480  //nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(scope);
2481  //if (!nscope.isEmpty())
2482  //{
2483  nd = getResolvedNamespace(scope);
2484  //}
2485  }
2486  QCString def;
2487 
2488  // determine the definition of the global variable
2489  if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@' &&
2490  !Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES)
2491  )
2492  // variable is inside a namespace, so put the scope before the name
2493  {
2494  SrcLangExt lang = nd->getLanguage();
2495  QCString sep=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
2496 
2497  if (!root->type.isEmpty())
2498  {
2499  if (root->spec&Entry::Alias) // turn 'typedef B NS::A' into 'using NS::A = B'
2500  {
2501  def="using "+nd->name()+sep+name+" = "+root->type;
2502  }
2503  else // normal member
2504  {
2505  def=root->type+" "+nd->name()+sep+name+root->args;
2506  }
2507  }
2508  else
2509  {
2510  def=nd->name()+sep+name+root->args;
2511  }
2512  }
2513  else
2514  {
2515  if (!root->type.isEmpty() && !root->name.isEmpty())
2516  {
2517  if (name.at(0)=='@') // dummy variable representing anonymous union
2518  {
2519  def=root->type;
2520  }
2521  else
2522  {
2523  if (root->spec&Entry::Alias) // turn 'typedef B A' into 'using A = B'
2524  {
2525  def="using "+root->name+" = "+root->type.mid(7);
2526  }
2527  else // normal member
2528  {
2529  def=root->type+" "+name+root->args;
2530  }
2531  }
2532  }
2533  else
2534  {
2535  def=name+root->args;
2536  }
2537  }
2538  def.stripPrefix("static ");
2539 
2540  MemberName *mn=Doxygen::functionNameSDict->find(name);
2541  if (mn)
2542  {
2543  //QCString nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(scope);
2544  //NamespaceDef *nd=0;
2545  //if (!nscope.isEmpty())
2546  if (!scope.isEmpty())
2547  {
2548  nd = getResolvedNamespace(scope);
2549  }
2550  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
2551  MemberDef *md;
2552  for (mni.toFirst();(md=mni.current());++mni)
2553  {
2554  if (
2555  ((nd==0 && md->getNamespaceDef()==0 && md->getFileDef() &&
2556  root->fileName==md->getFileDef()->absFilePath()
2557  ) // both variable names in the same file
2558  || (nd!=0 && md->getNamespaceDef()==nd) // both in same namespace
2559  )
2560  && !md->isDefine() // function style #define's can be "overloaded" by typedefs or variables
2561  && !md->isEnumerate() // in C# an enum value and enum can have the same name
2562  )
2563  // variable already in the scope
2564  {
2565  bool isPHPArray = md->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_PHP &&
2566  md->argsString()!=root->args &&
2567  root->args.find('[')!=-1;
2568  bool staticsInDifferentFiles =
2569  root->stat && md->isStatic() &&
2570  root->fileName!=md->getDefFileName();
2571 
2572  if (md->getFileDef() &&
2573  !isPHPArray && // not a php array
2574  !staticsInDifferentFiles
2575  )
2576  // not a php array variable
2577  {
2578 
2579  Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0,
2580  " variable already found: scope=%s\n",qPrint(md->getOuterScope()->name()));
2581  addMemberDocs(rootNav,md,def,0,FALSE);
2582  md->setRefItems(root->sli);
2583  return md;
2584  }
2585  }
2586  }
2587  }
2588 
2589  QCString fileName = root->fileName;
2590  if (fileName.isEmpty() && rootNav->tagInfo())
2591  {
2592  fileName = rootNav->tagInfo()->tagName;
2593  }
2594 
2595  Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0,
2596  " new variable, nd=%s tagInfo=%p!\n",nd?qPrint(nd->name()):"<global>",rootNav->tagInfo());
2597  // new global variable, enum value or typedef
2598  MemberDef *md=new MemberDef(
2599  fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
2600  root->type,name,root->args,0,
2601  root->protection, Normal,root->stat,Member,
2602  mtype,root->tArgLists ? root->tArgLists->getLast() : 0,0);
2603  md->setTagInfo(rootNav->tagInfo());
2604  md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
2605  md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
2606  md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
2607  md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
2608  md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
2609  md->setFromAnonymousScope(fromAnnScope);
2610  md->setFromAnonymousMember(fromAnnMemb);
2611  md->setInitializer(root->initializer);
2612  md->setMaxInitLines(root->initLines);
2613  md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
2614  md->setDefinition(def);
2615  md->setLanguage(root->lang);
2616  md->setId(root->id);
2617  md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
2618  md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
2619  md->setExplicitExternal(root->explicitExternal);
2620  //md->setOuterScope(fd);
2621  if (!root->explicitExternal)
2622  {
2623  md->setBodySegment(root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
2624  md->setBodyDef(fd);
2625  }
2626  addMemberToGroups(root,md);
2627 
2628  md->setRefItems(root->sli);
2629  if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@')
2630  {
2631  md->setNamespace(nd);
2632  nd->insertMember(md);
2633  }
2634 
2635  // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already inserted
2636  // it into the namespace.
2637  if (fd)
2638  {
2639  md->setFileDef(fd);
2640  fd->insertMember(md);
2641  }
2642 
2643  // add member definition to the list of globals
2644  if (mn)
2645  {
2646  mn->append(md);
2647  }
2648  else
2649  {
2650  mn = new MemberName(name);
2651  mn->append(md);
2652  Doxygen::functionNameSDict->append(name,mn);
2653  }
2654  rootNav->changeSection(Entry::EMPTY_SEC);
2655  return md;
2656 }
2657 
2662 static int findFunctionPtr(const QCString &type,int lang, int *pLength=0)
2663 {
2664  if (lang == SrcLangExt_Fortran || lang == SrcLangExt_VHDL)
2665  {
2666  return -1; // Fortran and VHDL do not have function pointers
2667  }
2668  static const QRegExp re("([^)]*[\\*\\^][^)]*)");
2669  int i=-1,l;
2670  int bb=type.find('<');
2671  int be=type.findRev('>');
2672  if (!type.isEmpty() && // return type is non-empty
2673  (i=re.match(type,0,&l))!=-1 && // contains (...*...)
2674  type.find("operator")==-1 && // not an operator
2675  (type.find(")(")==-1 || type.find("typedef ")!=-1) &&
2676  // not a function pointer return type
2677  !(bb<i && i<be) // bug665855: avoid treating "typedef A<void (T*)> type" as a function pointer
2678  )
2679  {
2680  if (pLength) *pLength=l;
2681  //printf("findFunctionPtr=%d\n",i);
2682  return i;
2683  }
2684  else
2685  {
2686  //printf("findFunctionPtr=%d\n",-1);
2687  return -1;
2688  }
2689 }
2690 
2691 
2695 static bool isVarWithConstructor(EntryNav *rootNav)
2696 {
2697  static QRegExp initChars("[0-9\"'&*!^]+");
2698  static QRegExp idChars("[a-z_A-Z][a-z_A-Z0-9]*");
2699  bool result=FALSE;
2700  bool typeIsClass;
2701  QCString type;
2702  Definition *ctx = 0;
2703  FileDef *fd = 0;
2704  int ti;
2705 
2706  //printf("isVarWithConstructor(%s)\n",rootNav->name().data());
2707  rootNav->loadEntry(g_storage);
2708  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
2709 
2710  if (rootNav->parent()->section() & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK)
2711  { // inside a class
2712  result=FALSE;
2713  goto done;
2714  }
2715  else if ((fd = rootNav->fileDef()) &&
2716  (fd->name().right(2)==".c" || fd->name().right(2)==".h")
2717  )
2718  { // inside a .c file
2719  result=FALSE;
2720  goto done;
2721  }
2722  if (root->type.isEmpty())
2723  {
2724  result=FALSE;
2725  goto done;
2726  }
2727  if (!rootNav->parent()->name().isEmpty())
2728  {
2729  ctx=Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(rootNav->parent()->name());
2730  }
2731  type = root->type;
2732  // remove qualifiers
2733  findAndRemoveWord(type,"const");
2734  findAndRemoveWord(type,"static");
2735  findAndRemoveWord(type,"volatile");
2736  //if (type.left(6)=="const ") type=type.right(type.length()-6);
2737  typeIsClass=getResolvedClass(ctx,fd,type)!=0;
2738  if (!typeIsClass && (ti=type.find('<'))!=-1)
2739  {
2740  typeIsClass=getResolvedClass(ctx,fd,type.left(ti))!=0;
2741  }
2742  if (typeIsClass) // now we still have to check if the arguments are
2743  // types or values. Since we do not have complete type info
2744  // we need to rely on heuristics :-(
2745  {
2746  //printf("typeIsClass\n");
2747  ArgumentList *al = root->argList;
2748  if (al==0 || al->isEmpty())
2749  {
2750  result=FALSE; // empty arg list -> function prototype.
2751  goto done;
2752  }
2753  ArgumentListIterator ali(*al);
2754  Argument *a;
2755  for (ali.toFirst();(a=ali.current());++ali)
2756  {
2757  if (!a->name.isEmpty() || !a->defval.isEmpty())
2758  {
2759  if (a->name.find(initChars)==0)
2760  {
2761  result=TRUE;
2762  }
2763  else
2764  {
2765  result=FALSE; // arg has (type,name) pair -> function prototype
2766  }
2767  goto done;
2768  }
2769  if (a->type.isEmpty() || getResolvedClass(ctx,fd,a->type)!=0)
2770  {
2771  result=FALSE; // arg type is a known type
2772  goto done;
2773  }
2774  if (checkIfTypedef(ctx,fd,a->type))
2775  {
2776  //printf("%s:%d: false (arg is typedef)\n",__FILE__,__LINE__);
2777  result=FALSE; // argument is a typedef
2778  goto done;
2779  }
2780  if (a->type.at(a->type.length()-1)=='*' ||
2781  a->type.at(a->type.length()-1)=='&')
2782  // type ends with * or & => pointer or reference
2783  {
2784  result=FALSE;
2785  goto done;
2786  }
2787  if (a->type.find(initChars)==0)
2788  {
2789  result=TRUE; // argument type starts with typical initializer char
2790  goto done;
2791  }
2792  QCString resType=resolveTypeDef(ctx,a->type);
2793  if (resType.isEmpty()) resType=a->type;
2794  int len;
2795  if (idChars.match(resType,0,&len)==0) // resType starts with identifier
2796  {
2797  resType=resType.left(len);
2798  //printf("resType=%s\n",resType.data());
2799  if (resType=="int" || resType=="long" || resType=="float" ||
2800  resType=="double" || resType=="char" || resType=="signed" ||
2801  resType=="const" || resType=="unsigned" || resType=="void")
2802  {
2803  result=FALSE; // type keyword -> function prototype
2804  goto done;
2805  }
2806  }
2807  }
2808  result=TRUE;
2809  }
2810 
2811 done:
2812  //printf("isVarWithConstructor(%s,%s)=%d\n",rootNav->parent()->name().data(),
2813  // root->type.data(),result);
2814  rootNav->releaseEntry();
2815  return result;
2816 }
2817 
2818 static void addVariable(EntryNav *rootNav,int isFuncPtr=-1)
2819 {
2820  rootNav->loadEntry(g_storage);
2821  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
2822 
2823  Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0,
2824  "VARIABLE_SEC: \n"
2825  " type=`%s' name=`%s' args=`%s' bodyLine=`%d' mGrpId=%d relates=%s\n",
2826  qPrint(root->type),
2827  qPrint(root->name),
2828  qPrint(root->args),
2829  root->bodyLine,
2830  root->mGrpId,
2831  qPrint(root->relates)
2832  );
2833  //printf("root->parent->name=%s\n",root->parent->name.data());
2834 
2835  if (root->type.isEmpty() && root->name.find("operator")==-1 &&
2836  (root->name.find('*')!=-1 || root->name.find('&')!=-1))
2837  {
2838  // recover from parse error caused by redundant braces
2839  // like in "int *(var[10]);", which is parsed as
2840  // type="" name="int *" args="(var[10])"
2841 
2842  root->type=root->name;
2843  static const QRegExp reName("[a-z_A-Z][a-z_A-Z0-9]*");
2844  int l=0;
2845  int i=root->args.isEmpty() ? -1 : reName.match(root->args,0,&l);
2846  if (i!=-1)
2847  {
2848  root->name=root->args.mid(i,l);
2849  root->args=root->args.mid(i+l,root->args.find(')',i+l)-i-l);
2850  }
2851  //printf("new: type=`%s' name=`%s' args=`%s'\n",
2852  // root->type.data(),root->name.data(),root->args.data());
2853  }
2854  else
2855  {
2856  int i=isFuncPtr;
2857  if (i==-1 && (root->spec&Entry::Alias)==0) i=findFunctionPtr(root->type,root->lang); // for typedefs isFuncPtr is not yet set
2858  Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0," functionPtr? %s\n",i!=-1?"yes":"no");
2859  if (i!=-1) // function pointer
2860  {
2861  int ai = root->type.find('[',i);
2862  if (ai>i) // function pointer array
2863  {
2864  root->args.prepend(root->type.right(root->type.length()-ai));
2865  root->type=root->type.left(ai);
2866  }
2867  else if (root->type.find(')',i)!=-1) // function ptr, not variable like "int (*bla)[10]"
2868  {
2869  root->type=root->type.left(root->type.length()-1);
2870  root->args.prepend(") ");
2871  //printf("root->type=%s root->args=%s\n",root->type.data(),root->args.data());
2872  }
2873  }
2874  }
2875 
2876  QCString scope,name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
2877 
2878  // find the scope of this variable
2879  EntryNav *p = rootNav->parent();
2880  while ((p->section() & Entry::SCOPE_MASK))
2881  {
2882  QCString scopeName = p->name();
2883  if (!scopeName.isEmpty())
2884  {
2885  scope.prepend(scopeName);
2886  break;
2887  }
2888  p=p->parent();
2889  }
2890 
2891  MemberType mtype;
2892  QCString type=root->type.stripWhiteSpace();
2893  ClassDef *cd=0;
2894  bool isRelated=FALSE;
2895  bool isMemberOf=FALSE;
2896 
2897  QCString classScope=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(scope);
2898  classScope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(classScope,FALSE);
2899  QCString annScopePrefix=scope.left(scope.length()-classScope.length());
2900 
2901  if (root->name.findRev("::")!=-1)
2902  {
2903  if (root->type=="friend class" || root->type=="friend struct" ||
2904  root->type=="friend union")
2905  {
2906  cd=getClass(scope);
2907  if (cd)
2908  {
2909  addVariableToClass(rootNav, // entry
2910  cd, // class to add member to
2911  MemberType_Friend, // type of member
2912  name, // name of the member
2913  FALSE, // from Anonymous scope
2914  0, // anonymous member
2915  Public, // protection
2916  Member // related to a class
2917  );
2918  }
2919  }
2920  goto nextMember;
2921  /* skip this member, because it is a
2922  * static variable definition (always?), which will be
2923  * found in a class scope as well, but then we know the
2924  * correct protection level, so only then it will be
2925  * inserted in the correct list!
2926  */
2927  }
2928 
2929  if (type=="@")
2930  mtype=MemberType_EnumValue;
2931  else if (type.left(8)=="typedef ")
2932  mtype=MemberType_Typedef;
2933  else if (type.left(7)=="friend ")
2934  mtype=MemberType_Friend;
2935  else if (root->mtype==Property)
2936  mtype=MemberType_Property;
2937  else if (root->mtype==Event)
2938  mtype=MemberType_Event;
2939  else
2940  mtype=MemberType_Variable;
2941 
2942  if (!root->relates.isEmpty()) // related variable
2943  {
2944  isRelated=TRUE;
2945  isMemberOf=(root->relatesType == MemberOf);
2946  if (getClass(root->relates)==0 && !scope.isEmpty())
2947  scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
2948  else
2949  scope=root->relates;
2950  }
2951 
2952  cd=getClass(scope);
2953  if (cd==0 && classScope!=scope) cd=getClass(classScope);
2954  if (cd)
2955  {
2956  MemberDef *md=0;
2957 
2958  // if cd is an anonymous (=tag less) scope we insert the member
2959  // into a non-anonymous parent scope as well. This is needed to
2960  // be able to refer to it using \var or \fn
2961 
2962  //int indentDepth=0;
2963  int si=scope.find('@');
2964  //int anonyScopes = 0;
2965  //bool added=FALSE;
2966 
2967  static bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
2968  if (si!=-1 && !inlineSimpleStructs) // anonymous scope or type
2969  {
2970  QCString pScope;
2971  ClassDef *pcd=0;
2972  pScope = scope.left(QMAX(si-2,0)); // scope without tag less parts
2973  if (!pScope.isEmpty())
2974  pScope.prepend(annScopePrefix);
2975  else if (annScopePrefix.length()>2)
2976  pScope=annScopePrefix.left(annScopePrefix.length()-2);
2977  if (name.at(0)!='@')
2978  {
2979  if (!pScope.isEmpty() && (pcd=getClass(pScope)))
2980  {
2981  md=addVariableToClass(rootNav, // entry
2982  pcd, // class to add member to
2983  mtype, // member type
2984  name, // member name
2985  TRUE, // from anonymous scope
2986  0, // from anonymous member
2987  root->protection,
2988  isMemberOf ? Foreign : isRelated ? Related : Member
2989  );
2990  //added=TRUE;
2991  }
2992  else // anonymous scope inside namespace or file => put variable in the global scope
2993  {
2994  if (mtype==MemberType_Variable)
2995  {
2996  md=addVariableToFile(rootNav,mtype,pScope,name,TRUE,0);
2997  }
2998  //added=TRUE;
2999  }
3000  }
3001  }
3002 
3003  //printf("name=`%s' scope=%s scope.right=%s\n",
3004  // name.data(),scope.data(),
3005  // scope.right(scope.length()-si).data());
3006  addVariableToClass(rootNav, // entry
3007  cd, // class to add member to
3008  mtype, // member type
3009  name, // name of the member
3010  FALSE, // from anonymous scope
3011  md, // from anonymous member
3012  root->protection,
3013  isMemberOf ? Foreign : isRelated ? Related : Member);
3014  }
3015  else if (!name.isEmpty()) // global variable
3016  {
3017  //printf("Inserting member in global scope %s!\n",scope.data());
3018  addVariableToFile(rootNav,mtype,scope,name,FALSE,/*0,*/0);
3019  }
3020 
3021 nextMember:
3022  rootNav->releaseEntry();
3023 }
3024 
3025 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
3026 // Searches the Entry tree for typedef documentation sections.
3027 // If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3028 static void buildTypedefList(EntryNav *rootNav)
3029 {
3030  //printf("buildVarList(%s)\n",rootNav->name().data());
3031  if (!rootNav->name().isEmpty() &&
3032  rootNav->section()==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
3033  rootNav->type().find("typedef ")!=-1 // its a typedef
3034  )
3035  {
3036  addVariable(rootNav);
3037  }
3038  if (rootNav->children())
3039  {
3040  EntryNavListIterator eli(*rootNav->children());
3041  EntryNav *e;
3042  for (;(e=eli.current());++eli)
3043  {
3044  if (e->section()!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3045  {
3046  buildTypedefList(e);
3047  }
3048  }
3049  }
3050 }
3051 
3052 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
3053 // Searches the Entry tree for Variable documentation sections.
3054 // If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3055 
3056 static void buildVarList(EntryNav *rootNav)
3057 {
3058  //printf("buildVarList(%s) section=%08x\n",rootNav->name().data(),rootNav->section());
3059  int isFuncPtr=-1;
3060  if (!rootNav->name().isEmpty() &&
3061  (rootNav->type().isEmpty() || g_compoundKeywordDict.find(rootNav->type())==0) &&
3062  (
3063  (rootNav->section()==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC // it's a variable
3064  ) ||
3065  (rootNav->section()==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // or maybe a function pointer variable
3066  (isFuncPtr=findFunctionPtr(rootNav->type(),rootNav->lang()))!=-1
3067  ) ||
3068  (rootNav->section()==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // class variable initialized by constructor
3069  isVarWithConstructor(rootNav)
3070  )
3071  )
3072  ) // documented variable
3073  {
3074  addVariable(rootNav,isFuncPtr);
3075  }
3076  if (rootNav->children())
3077  {
3078  EntryNavListIterator eli(*rootNav->children());
3079  EntryNav *e;
3080  for (;(e=eli.current());++eli)
3081  {
3082  if (e->section()!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3083  {
3084  buildVarList(e);
3085  }
3086  }
3087  }
3088 }
3089 
3090 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
3091 // Searches the Entry tree for Interface sections (UNO IDL only).
3092 // If found they are stored in their service or in the global list.
3093 //
3094 
3095 static void addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(
3096  EntryNav *const rootNav,
3097  ClassDef *const cd,
3098  QCString const& rname)
3099 {
3100  Entry *const root = rootNav->entry();
3101  FileDef *const fd = rootNav->fileDef();
3102  enum MemberType const type = (rootNav->section()==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC)
3103  ? MemberType_Interface
3104  : MemberType_Service;
3105  QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3106  if (fileName.isEmpty() && rootNav->tagInfo())
3107  {
3108  fileName = rootNav->tagInfo()->tagName;
3109  }
3110  MemberDef *const md = new MemberDef(
3111  fileName, root->startLine, root->startColumn, root->type, rname,
3112  "", "", root->protection, root->virt, root->stat, Member,
3113  type, 0, root->argList);
3114  md->setTagInfo(rootNav->tagInfo());
3115  md->setMemberClass(cd);
3116  md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3117  md->setDocsForDefinition(false);
3118  md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3119  md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3120  md->setBodySegment(root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3121  md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3122  md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3123  md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3124  md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3125  md->setBodyDef(fd);
3126  md->setFileDef(fd);
3127  md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3128  QCString const def = root->type + " " + rname;
3129  md->setDefinition(def);
3130  md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3131  md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3132 
3133  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3134  " Interface Member:\n"
3135  " `%s' `%s' proto=%d\n"
3136  " def=`%s'\n",
3137  qPrint(root->type),
3138  qPrint(rname),
3139  root->proto,
3140  qPrint(def)
3141  );
3142 
3143  // add member to the global list of all members
3144  MemberName *mn;
3145  if ((mn=Doxygen::memberNameSDict->find(rname)))
3146  {
3147  mn->append(md);
3148  }
3149  else
3150  {
3151  mn = new MemberName(rname);
3152  mn->append(md);
3153  Doxygen::memberNameSDict->append(rname,mn);
3154  }
3155 
3156  // add member to the class cd
3157  cd->insertMember(md);
3158  // also add the member as a "base" (to get nicer diagrams)
3159  // "optional" interface/service get Protected which turns into dashed line
3160  BaseInfo base(rname,
3161  (root->spec & (Entry::Optional)) ? Protected : Public,Normal);
3162  findClassRelation(rootNav,cd,cd,&base,0,DocumentedOnly,true)
3163  || findClassRelation(rootNav,cd,cd,&base,0,Undocumented,true);
3164  // add file to list of used files
3165  cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3166 
3167  addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3168  rootNav->changeSection(Entry::EMPTY_SEC);
3169  md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3170 }
3171 
3172 static void buildInterfaceAndServiceList(EntryNav *const rootNav)
3173 {
3174  if (rootNav->section()==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC ||
3175  rootNav->section()==Entry::INCLUDED_SERVICE_SEC)
3176  {
3177  rootNav->loadEntry(g_storage);
3178  Entry *const root = rootNav->entry();
3179 
3180  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3181  "EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC:\n"
3182  " `%s' `%s'::`%s' `%s' relates=`%s' relatesType=`%d' file=`%s' line=`%d' bodyLine=`%d' #tArgLists=%d mGrpId=%d spec=%lld proto=%d docFile=%s\n",
3183  qPrint(root->type),
3184  qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()),
3185  qPrint(root->name),
3186  qPrint(root->args),
3187  qPrint(root->relates),
3188  root->relatesType,
3189  qPrint(root->fileName),
3190  root->startLine,
3191  root->bodyLine,
3192  root->tArgLists ? (int)root->tArgLists->count() : -1,
3193  root->mGrpId,
3194  root->spec,
3195  root->proto,
3196  qPrint(root->docFile)
3197  );
3198 
3199  QCString const rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3200 
3201  if (!rname.isEmpty())
3202  {
3203  QCString const scope = rootNav->parent()->name();
3204  ClassDef *const cd = getClass(scope);
3205  assert(cd);
3206  if (cd && ((ClassDef::Interface == cd->compoundType()) ||
3207  (ClassDef::Service == cd->compoundType()) ||
3208  (ClassDef::Singleton == cd->compoundType())))
3209  {
3210  addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(rootNav,cd,rname);
3211  }
3212  else
3213  {
3214  assert(false); // was checked by scanner.l
3215  }
3216  }
3217  else if (rname.isEmpty())
3218  {
3219  warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3220  "Illegal member name found.");
3221  }
3222 
3223  rootNav->releaseEntry();
3224  }
3225  // can only have these in IDL anyway
3226  switch (rootNav->lang())
3227  {
3228  case SrcLangExt_Unknown: // fall through (root node always is Unknown)
3229  case SrcLangExt_IDL:
3230  RECURSE_ENTRYTREE(buildInterfaceAndServiceList,rootNav);
3231  break;
3232  default:
3233  return; // nothing to do here
3234  }
3235 }

3238 //----------------------------------------------------------------------
3239 // Searches the Entry tree for Function sections.
3240 // If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3241 
3242 static void addMethodToClass(EntryNav *rootNav,ClassDef *cd,
3243  const QCString &rname,bool isFriend)
3244 {
3245  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
3246  FileDef *fd=rootNav->fileDef();
3247 
3248  int l;
3249  static QRegExp re("([a-z_A-Z0-9: ]*[ &*]+[ ]*");
3250  int ts=root->type.find('<');
3251  int te=root->type.findRev('>');
3252  int i=re.match(root->type,0,&l);
3253  if (i!=-1 && ts!=-1 && ts<te && ts<i && i<te) // avoid changing A<int(int*)>, see bug 677315
3254  {
3255  i=-1;
3256  }
3257 
3258  if (cd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp && // only C has pointers
3259  !root->type.isEmpty() && (root->spec&Entry::Alias)==0 && i!=-1) // function variable
3260  {
3261  root->args+=root->type.right(root->type.length()-i-l);
3262  root->type=root->type.left(i+l);
3263  }
3264 
3265  QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3266  if (name.left(2)=="::") name=name.right(name.length()-2);
3267 
3268  MemberType mtype;
3269  if (isFriend) mtype=MemberType_Friend;
3270  else if (root->mtype==Signal) mtype=MemberType_Signal;
3271  else if (root->mtype==Slot) mtype=MemberType_Slot;
3272  else if (root->mtype==DCOP) mtype=MemberType_DCOP;
3273  else mtype=MemberType_Function;
3274 
3275  // strip redundant template specifier for constructors
3276  if ((fd==0 || fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp) &&
3277  name.left(9)!="operator " && (i=name.find('<'))!=-1 && name.find('>')!=-1)
3278  {
3279  name=name.left(i);
3280  }
3281 
3282  QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3283  if (fileName.isEmpty() && rootNav->tagInfo())
3284  {
3285  fileName = rootNav->tagInfo()->tagName;
3286  }
3287 
3288  //printf("root->name=`%s; root->args=`%s' root->argList=`%s'\n",
3289  // root->name.data(),root->args.data(),argListToString(root->argList).data()
3290  // );
3291 
3292  // adding class member
3293  MemberDef *md=new MemberDef(
3294  fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3295  root->type,name,root->args,root->exception,
3296  root->protection,root->virt,
3297  root->stat && root->relatesType != MemberOf,
3298  root->relates.isEmpty() ? Member :
3299  root->relatesType == MemberOf ? Foreign : Related,
3300  mtype,root->tArgLists ? root->tArgLists->getLast() : 0,root->argList);
3301  md->setTagInfo(rootNav->tagInfo());
3302  md->setMemberClass(cd);
3303  md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3304  md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3305  md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3306  md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3307  md->setBodySegment(root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3308  md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3309  md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3310  md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3311  md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3312  md->setId(root->id);
3313  md->setBodyDef(fd);
3314  md->setFileDef(fd);
3315  //md->setScopeTemplateArguments(root->tArgList);
3316  md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3317  QCString def;
3318  QCString qualScope = cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
3319  SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
3320  QCString scopeSeparator=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
3321  if (scopeSeparator!="::")
3322  {
3323  qualScope = substitute(qualScope,"::",scopeSeparator);
3324  }
3325  if (lang==SrcLangExt_PHP)
3326  {
3327  // for PHP we use Class::method and Namespace\method
3328  scopeSeparator="::";
3329  }
3330  if (!root->relates.isEmpty() || isFriend || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
3331  {
3332  if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3333  {
3334  if (root->argList)
3335  {
3336  def=root->type+" "+name;
3337  }
3338  else
3339  {
3340  def=root->type+" "+name+root->args;
3341  }
3342  }
3343  else
3344  {
3345  if (root->argList)
3346  {
3347  def=name;
3348  }
3349  else
3350  {
3351  def=name+root->args;
3352  }
3353  }
3354  }
3355  else
3356  {
3357  if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3358  {
3359  if (root->argList)
3360  {
3361  def=root->type+" "+qualScope+scopeSeparator+name;
3362  }
3363  else
3364  {
3365  def=root->type+" "+qualScope+scopeSeparator+name+root->args;
3366  }
3367  }
3368  else
3369  {
3370  if (root->argList)
3371  {
3372  def=qualScope+scopeSeparator+name;
3373  }
3374  else
3375  {
3376  def=qualScope+scopeSeparator+name+root->args;
3377  }
3378  }
3379  }
3380  if (def.left(7)=="friend ") def=def.right(def.length()-7);
3381  md->setDefinition(def);
3382  md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3383  md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3384 
3385  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3386  " Func Member:\n"
3387  " `%s' `%s'::`%s' `%s' proto=%d\n"
3388  " def=`%s'\n",
3389  qPrint(root->type),
3390  qPrint(qualScope),
3391  qPrint(rname),
3392  qPrint(root->args),
3393  root->proto,
3394  qPrint(def)
3395  );
3396 
3397  // add member to the global list of all members
3398  //printf("Adding member=%s class=%s\n",md->name().data(),cd->name().data());
3399  MemberName *mn;
3400  if ((mn=Doxygen::memberNameSDict->find(name)))
3401  {
3402  mn->append(md);
3403  }
3404  else
3405  {
3406  mn = new MemberName(name);
3407  mn->append(md);
3408  Doxygen::memberNameSDict->append(name,mn);
3409  }
3410 
3411  // add member to the class cd
3412  cd->insertMember(md);
3413  // add file to list of used files
3414  cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3415 
3416  addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3417  rootNav->changeSection(Entry::EMPTY_SEC);
3418  md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3419 }
3420 
3421 
3422 static void buildFunctionList(EntryNav *rootNav)
3423 {
3424  if (rootNav->section()==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC)
3425  {
3426  rootNav->loadEntry(g_storage);
3427  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
3428 
3429  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3430  "FUNCTION_SEC:\n"
3431  " `%s' `%s'::`%s' `%s' relates=`%s' relatesType=`%d' file=`%s' line=`%d' bodyLine=`%d' #tArgLists=%d mGrpId=%d spec=%lld proto=%d docFile=%s\n",
3432  qPrint(root->type),
3433  qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()),
3434  qPrint(root->name),
3435  qPrint(root->args),
3436  qPrint(root->relates),
3437  root->relatesType,
3438  qPrint(root->fileName),
3439  root->startLine,
3440  root->bodyLine,
3441  root->tArgLists ? (int)root->tArgLists->count() : -1,
3442  root->mGrpId,
3443  root->spec,
3444  root->proto,
3445  qPrint(root->docFile)
3446  );
3447 
3448  bool isFriend=root->type.find("friend ")!=-1;
3449  QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3450  //printf("rname=%s\n",rname.data());
3451 
3452  QCString scope=rootNav->parent()->name(); //stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent->name);
3453  if (!rname.isEmpty() && scope.find('@')==-1)
3454  {
3455  ClassDef *cd=0;
3456  // check if this function's parent is a class
3457  scope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(scope,FALSE);
3458 
3459  FileDef *rfd=rootNav->fileDef();
3460 
3461  int memIndex=rname.findRev("::");
3462 
3463  cd=getClass(scope);
3464  if (cd && scope+"::"==rname.left(scope.length()+2)) // found A::f inside A
3465  {
3466  // strip scope from name
3467  rname=rname.right(rname.length()-rootNav->parent()->name().length()-2);
3468  }
3469 
3470  NamespaceDef *nd = 0;
3471  bool isMember=FALSE;
3472  if (memIndex!=-1)
3473  {
3474  int ts=rname.find('<');
3475  int te=rname.find('>');
3476  if (memIndex>0 && (ts==-1 || te==-1))
3477  {
3478  // note: the following code was replaced by inMember=TRUE to deal with a
3479  // function rname='X::foo' of class X inside a namespace also called X...
3480  // bug id 548175
3481  //nd = Doxygen::namespaceSDict->find(rname.left(memIndex));
3482  //isMember = nd==0;
3483  //if (nd)
3484  //{
3485  // // strip namespace scope from name
3486  // scope=rname.left(memIndex);
3487  // rname=rname.right(rname.length()-memIndex-2);
3488  //}
3489  isMember = TRUE;
3490  }
3491  else
3492  {
3493  isMember=memIndex<ts || memIndex>te;
3494  }
3495  }
3496 
3497  static QRegExp re("([a-z_A-Z0-9: ]*[ &*]+[ ]*");
3498  int ts=root->type.find('<');
3499  int te=root->type.findRev('>');
3500  int ti;
3501  if (!rootNav->parent()->name().isEmpty() &&
3502  (rootNav->parent()->section() & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK) &&
3503  cd &&
3504  // do some fuzzy things to exclude function pointers
3505  (root->type.isEmpty() ||
3506  ((ti=root->type.find(re,0))==-1 || // type does not contain ..(..*
3507  (ts!=-1 && ts<te && ts<ti && ti<te) || // outside of < ... >
3508  root->args.find(")[")!=-1) || // and args not )[.. -> function pointer
3509  root->type.find(")(")!=-1 || root->type.find("operator")!=-1 || // type contains ..)(.. and not "operator"
3510  cd->getLanguage()!=SrcLangExt_Cpp // language other than C
3511  )
3512  )
3513  {
3514  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> member %s of class %s!\n",
3515  qPrint(rname),qPrint(cd->name()));
3516  addMethodToClass(rootNav,cd,rname,isFriend);
3517  }
3518  else if (!((rootNav->parent()->section() & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK)
3519  || rootNav->parent()->section()==Entry::OBJCIMPL_SEC
3520  ) &&
3521  !isMember &&
3522  (root->relates.isEmpty() || root->relatesType == Duplicate) &&
3523  root->type.left(7)!="extern " && root->type.left(8)!="typedef "
3524  )
3525  // no member => unrelated function
3526  {
3527  /* check the uniqueness of the function name in the file.
3528  * A file could contain a function prototype and a function definition
3529  * or even multiple function prototypes.
3530  */
3531  bool found=FALSE;
3532  MemberName *mn;
3533  MemberDef *md=0;
3534  if ((mn=Doxygen::functionNameSDict->find(rname)))
3535  {
3536  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> function %s already found!\n",qPrint(rname));
3537  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
3538  for (mni.toFirst();(!found && (md=mni.current()));++mni)
3539  {
3540  NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
3541  NamespaceDef *rnd = 0;
3542  //printf("root namespace=%s\n",rootNav->parent()->name().data());
3543  QCString fullScope = scope;
3544  QCString parentScope = rootNav->parent()->name();
3545  if (!parentScope.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(parentScope,scope))
3546  {
3547  if (!scope.isEmpty()) fullScope.prepend("::");
3548  fullScope.prepend(parentScope);
3549  }
3550  //printf("fullScope=%s\n",fullScope.data());
3551  rnd = getResolvedNamespace(fullScope);
3552  FileDef *mfd = md->getFileDef();
3553  QCString nsName,rnsName;
3554  if (mnd) nsName = mnd->name().copy();
3555  if (rnd) rnsName = rnd->name().copy();
3556  //printf("matching arguments for %s%s %s%s\n",
3557  // md->name().data(),md->argsString(),rname.data(),argListToString(root->argList).data());
3558  ArgumentList *mdAl = md->argumentList();
3559  ArgumentList *mdTempl = md->templateArguments();
3560 
3561  // in case of template functions, we need to check if the
3562  // functions have the same number of template parameters
3563  bool sameNumTemplateArgs = TRUE;
3564  bool matchingReturnTypes = TRUE;
3565  if (mdTempl!=0 && root->tArgLists)
3566  {
3567  if (mdTempl->count()!=root->tArgLists->getLast()->count())
3568  {
3569  sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3570  }
3571  if (md->typeString()!=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->type))
3572  {
3573  matchingReturnTypes = FALSE;
3574  }
3575  }
3576 
3577  bool staticsInDifferentFiles =
3578  root->stat && md->isStatic() && root->fileName!=md->getDefFileName();
3579 
3580  if (
3581  matchArguments2(md->getOuterScope(),mfd,mdAl,
3582  rnd ? rnd : Doxygen::globalScope,rfd,root->argList,
3583  FALSE) &&
3584  sameNumTemplateArgs &&
3585  matchingReturnTypes &&
3586  !staticsInDifferentFiles
3587  )
3588  {
3589  GroupDef *gd=0;
3590  if (root->groups->getFirst()!=0)
3591  {
3592  gd = Doxygen::groupSDict->find(root->groups->getFirst()->groupname.data());
3593  }
3594  //printf("match!\n");
3595  //printf("mnd=%p rnd=%p nsName=%s rnsName=%s\n",mnd,rnd,nsName.data(),rnsName.data());
3596  // see if we need to create a new member
3597  found=(mnd && rnd && nsName==rnsName) || // members are in the same namespace
3598  ((mnd==0 && rnd==0 && mfd!=0 && // no external reference and
3599  mfd->absFilePath()==root->fileName // prototype in the same file
3600  )
3601  );
3602  // otherwise, allow a duplicate global member with the same argument list
3603  if (!found && gd && gd==md->getGroupDef() && nsName==rnsName)
3604  {
3605  // member is already in the group, so we don't want to add it again.
3606  found=TRUE;
3607  }
3608 
3609  //printf("combining function with prototype found=%d in namespace %s\n",
3610  // found,nsName.data());
3611 
3612  if (found)
3613  {
3614  // merge argument lists
3615  mergeArguments(mdAl,root->argList,!root->doc.isEmpty());
3616  // merge documentation
3617  if (md->documentation().isEmpty() && !root->doc.isEmpty())
3618  {
3619  ArgumentList *argList = new ArgumentList;
3620  stringToArgumentList(root->args,argList);
3621  if (root->proto)
3622  {
3623  //printf("setDeclArgumentList to %p\n",argList);
3624  md->setDeclArgumentList(argList);
3625  }
3626  else
3627  {
3628  md->setArgumentList(argList);
3629  }
3630  }
3631 
3632  md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3633  md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3634  md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3635  if (md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
3636  {
3637  md->setBodySegment(root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3638  md->setBodyDef(rfd);
3639  }
3640 
3641  if (md->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !root->brief.isEmpty())
3642  {
3643  md->setArgsString(root->args);
3644  }
3645  md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3646 
3647  md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3648 
3649  md->enableCallGraph(md->hasCallGraph() || root->callGraph);
3650  md->enableCallerGraph(md->hasCallerGraph() || root->callerGraph);
3651 
3652  // merge ingroup specifiers
3653  if (md->getGroupDef()==0 && root->groups->getFirst()!=0)
3654  {
3655  addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3656  }
3657  else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && root->groups->count()==0)
3658  {
3659  //printf("existing member is grouped, new member not\n");
3660  root->groups->append(new Grouping(md->getGroupDef()->name(), md->getGroupPri()));
3661  }
3662  else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && root->groups->getFirst()!=0)
3663  {
3664  //printf("both members are grouped\n");
3665  }
3666 
3667  // if md is a declaration and root is the corresponding
3668  // definition, then turn md into a definition.
3669  if (md->isPrototype() && !root->proto)
3670  {
3671  md->setPrototype(FALSE);
3672  }
3673  }
3674  }
3675  }
3676  }
3677  if (!found) /* global function is unique with respect to the file */
3678  {
3679  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> new function %s found!\n",qPrint(rname));
3680  //printf("New function type=`%s' name=`%s' args=`%s' bodyLine=%d\n",
3681  // root->type.data(),rname.data(),root->args.data(),root->bodyLine);
3682 
3683  // new global function
3684  ArgumentList *tArgList = root->tArgLists ? root->tArgLists->getLast() : 0;
3685  QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3686  md=new MemberDef(
3687  root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3688  root->type,name,root->args,root->exception,
3689  root->protection,root->virt,root->stat,Member,
3690  MemberType_Function,tArgList,root->argList);
3691 
3692  md->setTagInfo(rootNav->tagInfo());
3693  md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3694  md->setId(root->id);
3695  //md->setDefFile(root->fileName);
3696  //md->setDefLine(root->startLine);
3697  md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3698  md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3699  md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3700  md->setPrototype(root->proto);
3701  md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3702  md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3703  //md->setBody(root->body);
3704  md->setBodySegment(root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3705  FileDef *fd=rootNav->fileDef();
3706  md->setBodyDef(fd);
3707  md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3708  md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3709  md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3710 
3711  // see if the function is inside a namespace that was not part of
3712  // the name already (in that case nd should be non-zero already)
3713  if (nd==0 && rootNav->parent()->section() == Entry::NAMESPACE_SEC )
3714  {
3715  //QCString nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(rootNav->parent()->name());
3716  QCString nscope=rootNav->parent()->name();
3717  if (!nscope.isEmpty())
3718  {
3719  nd = getResolvedNamespace(nscope);
3720  }
3721  }
3722 
3723  if (!scope.isEmpty())
3724  {
3725  QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(root->lang);
3726  if (sep!="::")
3727  {
3728  scope = substitute(scope,"::",sep);
3729  }
3730  scope+=sep;
3731  }
3732 
3733  QCString def;
3734  if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3735  {
3736  if (root->argList)
3737  {
3738  def=root->type+" "+scope+name;
3739  }
3740  else
3741  {
3742  def=root->type+" "+scope+name+root->args;
3743  }
3744  }
3745  else
3746  {
3747  if (root->argList)
3748  {
3749  def=scope+name.copy();
3750  }
3751  else
3752  {
3753  def=scope+name+root->args;
3754  }
3755  }
3756  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3757  " Global Function:\n"
3758  " `%s' `%s'::`%s' `%s' proto=%d\n"
3759  " def=`%s'\n",
3760  qPrint(root->type),
3761  qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()),
3762  qPrint(rname),
3763  qPrint(root->args),
3764  root->proto,
3765  qPrint(def)
3766  );
3767  md->setDefinition(def);
3768  md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3769  md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3770  //if (root->mGrpId!=-1)
3771  //{
3772  // md->setMemberGroup(memberGroupDict[root->mGrpId]);
3773  //}
3774 
3775  md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3776  if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@')
3777  {
3778  // add member to namespace
3779  md->setNamespace(nd);
3780  nd->insertMember(md);
3781  }
3782  if (fd)
3783  {
3784  // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3785  // inserted it into the namespace)
3786  md->setFileDef(fd);
3787  fd->insertMember(md);
3788  }
3789 
3790  // add member to the list of file members
3791  //printf("Adding member=%s\n",md->name().data());
3792  MemberName *mn;
3793  if ((mn=Doxygen::functionNameSDict->find(name)))
3794  {
3795  mn->append(md);
3796  }
3797  else
3798  {
3799  mn = new MemberName(name);
3800  mn->append(md);
3801  Doxygen::functionNameSDict->append(name,mn);
3802  }
3803  addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3804  if (root->relatesType == Simple) // if this is a relatesalso command,
3805  // allow find Member to pick it up
3806  {
3807  rootNav->changeSection(Entry::EMPTY_SEC); // Otherwise we have finished
3808  // with this entry.
3809 
3810  }
3811  }
3812  else
3813  {
3814  FileDef *fd=rootNav->fileDef();
3815  if (fd)
3816  {
3817  // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3818  // inserted it into the namespace)
3819  fd->insertMember(md);
3820  }
3821  }
3822 
3823  //printf("unrelated function %d `%s' `%s' `%s'\n",
3824  // root->parent->section,root->type.data(),rname.data(),root->args.data());
3825  }
3826  else
3827  {
3828  Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> %s not processed!\n",qPrint(rname));
3829  }
3830  }
3831  else if (rname.isEmpty())
3832  {
3833  warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3834  "Illegal member name found."
3835  );
3836  }
3837 
3838  rootNav->releaseEntry();
3839  }
3840  RECURSE_ENTRYTREE(buildFunctionList,rootNav);
3841 }

3845 static void findFriends()
3846 {
3847  //printf("findFriends()\n");
3848  MemberNameSDict::Iterator fnli(*Doxygen::functionNameSDict);
3849  MemberName *fn;
3850  for (;(fn=fnli.current());++fnli) // for each global function name
3851  {
3852  //printf("Function name=`%s'\n",fn->memberName());
3853  MemberName *mn;
3854  if ((mn=Doxygen::memberNameSDict->find(fn->memberName())))
3855  { // there are members with the same name
3856  //printf("Function name is also a member name\n");
3857  MemberNameIterator fni(*fn);
3858  MemberDef *fmd;
3859  for (;(fmd=fni.current());++fni) // for each function with that name
3860  {
3861  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
3862  MemberDef *mmd;
3863  for (;(mmd=mni.current());++mni) // for each member with that name
3864  {
3865  //printf("Checking for matching arguments
3866  // mmd->isRelated()=%d mmd->isFriend()=%d mmd->isFunction()=%d\n",
3867  // mmd->isRelated(),mmd->isFriend(),mmd->isFunction());
3868  ArgumentList *mmdAl = mmd->argumentList();
3869  ArgumentList *fmdAl = fmd->argumentList();
3870  if ((mmd->isFriend() || (mmd->isRelated() && mmd->isFunction())) &&
3871  matchArguments2(mmd->getOuterScope(), mmd->getFileDef(), mmdAl,
3872  fmd->getOuterScope(), fmd->getFileDef(), fmdAl,
3873  TRUE
3874  )
3875 
3876  ) // if the member is related and the arguments match then the
3877  // function is actually a friend.
3878  {
3879  mergeArguments(mmdAl,fmdAl);
3880  if (!fmd->documentation().isEmpty())
3881  {
3882  mmd->setDocumentation(fmd->documentation(),fmd->docFile(),fmd->docLine());
3883  }
3884  else if (!mmd->documentation().isEmpty())
3885  {
3886  fmd->setDocumentation(mmd->documentation(),mmd->docFile(),mmd->docLine());
3887  }
3888  if (mmd->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty())
3889  {
3890  mmd->setBriefDescription(fmd->briefDescription(),fmd->briefFile(),fmd->briefLine());
3891  }
3892  else if (!mmd->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty())
3893  {
3894  fmd->setBriefDescription(mmd->briefDescription(),mmd->briefFile(),mmd->briefLine());
3895  }
3896  if (!fmd->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
3897  {
3898  mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(fmd->inbodyDocumentation(),fmd->inbodyFile(),fmd->inbodyLine());
3899  }
3900  else if (!mmd->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
3901  {
3902  fmd->setInbodyDocumentation(mmd->inbodyDocumentation(),mmd->inbodyFile(),mmd->inbodyLine());
3903  }
3904  //printf("body mmd %d fmd %d\n",mmd->getStartBodyLine(),fmd->getStartBodyLine());
3905  if (mmd->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && fmd->getStartBodyLine()!=-1)
3906  {
3907  mmd->setBodySegment(fmd->getStartBodyLine(),fmd->getEndBodyLine());
3908  mmd->setBodyDef(fmd->getBodyDef());
3909  //mmd->setBodyMember(fmd);
3910  }
3911  else if (mmd->getStartBodyLine()!=-1 && fmd->getStartBodyLine()==-1)
3912  {
3913  fmd->setBodySegment(mmd->getStartBodyLine(),mmd->getEndBodyLine());
3914  fmd->setBodyDef(mmd->getBodyDef());
3915  //fmd->setBodyMember(mmd);
3916  }
3917  mmd->setDocsForDefinition(fmd->isDocsForDefinition());
3918 
3919  mmd->enableCallGraph(mmd->hasCallGraph() || fmd->hasCallGraph());
3920  mmd->enableCallerGraph(mmd->hasCallerGraph() || fmd->hasCallerGraph());
3921  fmd->enableCallGraph(mmd->hasCallGraph() || fmd->hasCallGraph());
3922  fmd->enableCallerGraph(mmd->hasCallerGraph() || fmd->hasCallerGraph());
3923  }
3924  }
3925  }
3926  }
3927  }
3928 }

3932 static void transferFunctionDocumentation()
3933 {
3934  //printf("---- transferFunctionDocumentation()\n");
3935 
3936  // find matching function declaration and definitions.
3937  MemberNameSDict::Iterator mnli(*Doxygen::functionNameSDict);
3938  MemberName *mn;
3939  for (;(mn=mnli.current());++mnli)
3940  {
3941  //printf("memberName=%s count=%d\n",mn->memberName(),mn->count());
3942  MemberDef *mdef=0,*mdec=0;
3943  MemberNameIterator mni1(*mn);
3944  /* find a matching function declaration and definition for this function */
3945  for (;(mdec=mni1.current());++mni1)
3946  {
3947  if (mdec->isPrototype() ||
3948  (mdec->isVariable() && mdec->isExternal())
3949  )
3950  {
3951  MemberNameIterator mni2(*mn);
3952  for (;(mdef=mni2.current());++mni2)
3953  {
3954  combineDeclarationAndDefinition(mdec,mdef);
3955  }
3956  }
3957  }
3958  }
3959 }

3963 static void transferFunctionReferences()
3964 {
3965  MemberNameSDict::Iterator mnli(*Doxygen::functionNameSDict);
3966  MemberName *mn;
3967  for (;(mn=mnli.current());++mnli)
3968  {
3969  MemberDef *md,*mdef=0,*mdec=0;
3970  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
3971  /* find a matching function declaration and definition for this function */
3972  for (;(md=mni.current());++mni)
3973  {
3974  if (md->isPrototype())
3975  mdec=md;
3976  else if (md->isVariable() && md->isExternal())
3977  mdec=md;
3978 
3979  if (md->isFunction() && !md->isStatic() && !md->isPrototype())
3980  mdef=md;
3981  else if (md->isVariable() && !md->isExternal() && !md->isStatic())
3982  mdef=md;
3983  }
3984  if (mdef && mdec)
3985  {
3986  ArgumentList *mdefAl = mdef->argumentList();
3987  ArgumentList *mdecAl = mdec->argumentList();
3988  if (
3989  matchArguments2(mdef->getOuterScope(),mdef->getFileDef(),mdefAl,
3990  mdec->getOuterScope(),mdec->getFileDef(),mdecAl,
3991  TRUE
3992  )
3993  ) /* match found */
3994  {
3995  MemberSDict *defDict = mdef->getReferencesMembers();
3996  MemberSDict *decDict = mdec->getReferencesMembers();
3997  if (defDict!=0)
3998  {
3999  MemberSDict::IteratorDict msdi(*defDict);
4000  MemberDef *rmd;
4001  for (msdi.toFirst();(rmd=msdi.current());++msdi)
4002  {
4003  if (decDict==0 || decDict->find(rmd->name())==0)
4004  {
4005  mdec->addSourceReferences(rmd);
4006  }
4007  }
4008  }
4009  if (decDict!=0)
4010  {
4011  MemberSDict::IteratorDict msdi(*decDict);
4012  MemberDef *rmd;
4013  for (msdi.toFirst();(rmd=msdi.current());++msdi)
4014  {
4015  if (defDict==0 || defDict->find(rmd->name())==0)
4016  {
4017  mdef->addSourceReferences(rmd);
4018  }
4019  }
4020  }
4021 
4022  defDict = mdef->getReferencedByMembers();
4023  decDict = mdec->getReferencedByMembers();
4024  if (defDict!=0)
4025  {
4026  MemberSDict::IteratorDict msdi(*defDict);
4027  MemberDef *rmd;
4028  for (msdi.toFirst();(rmd=msdi.current());++msdi)
4029  {
4030  if (decDict==0 || decDict->find(rmd->name())==0)
4031  {
4032  mdec->addSourceReferencedBy(rmd);
4033  }
4034  }
4035  }
4036  if (decDict!=0)
4037  {
4038  MemberSDict::IteratorDict msdi(*decDict);
4039  MemberDef *rmd;
4040  for (msdi.toFirst();(rmd=msdi.current());++msdi)
4041  {
4042  if (defDict==0 || defDict->find(rmd->name())==0)
4043  {
4044  mdef->addSourceReferencedBy(rmd);
4045  }
4046  }
4047  }
4048  }
4049  }
4050  }
4051 }

4054 
4055 static void transferRelatedFunctionDocumentation()
4056 {
4057  // find match between function declaration and definition for
4058  // related functions
4059  MemberNameSDict::Iterator mnli(*Doxygen::functionNameSDict);
4060  MemberName *mn;
4061  for (mnli.toFirst();(mn=mnli.current());++mnli)
4062  {
4063  MemberDef *md;
4064  MemberNameIterator mni(*mn);
4065  /* find a matching function declaration and definition for this function */
4066  for (mni.toFirst();(md=mni.current());++mni) // for each global function
4067  {
4068  //printf(" Function `%s'\n",md->name().data());
4069  MemberName *rmn;
4070  if ((rmn=Doxygen::memberNameSDict->find(md->name()))) // check if there is a member with the same name
4071  {
4072  //printf(" Member name found\n");
4073  MemberDef *rmd;
4074  MemberNameIterator rmni(*rmn);
4075  for (rmni.toFirst();(rmd=rmni.current());++rmni) // for each member with the same name
4076  {
4077  ArgumentList *mdAl = md->argumentList();
4078  ArgumentList *rmdAl = rmd->argumentList();
4079  //printf(" Member found: related=`%d'\n",rmd->isRelated());
4080  if ((rmd->isRelated() || rmd->isForeign()) && // related function
4081  matchArguments2( md->getOuterScope(), md->getFileDef(), mdAl,
4082  rmd->getOuterScope(),rmd->getFileDef(),rmdAl,
4083  TRUE
4084  )
4085  )
4086  {
4087  //printf(" Found related member `%s'\n",md->name().data());
4088  if (rmd->relatedAlso())
4089  md->setRelatedAlso(rmd->relatedAlso());
4090  else if (rmd->isForeign())
4091  md->makeForeign();
4092  else
4093  md->makeRelated();
4094  }
4095  }
4096  }
4097  }
4098  }
4099 }

4102 
4108 static QDict<int> *getTemplateArgumentsInName(ArgumentList *templateArguments,const QCString &name)
4109 {
4110  QDict<int> *templateNames = new QDict<int>(17);
4111  templateNames->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
4112  static QRegExp re("[a-z_A-Z][a-z_A-Z0-9:]*");
4113  if (templateArguments)
4114  {
4115  ArgumentListIterator ali(*templateArguments);
4116  Argument *arg;
4117  int count=0;
4118  for (ali.toFirst();(arg=ali.current());++ali,count++)
4119  {
4120  int i,p=0,l;
4121  while ((i=re.match(name,p,&l))!=-1)
4122  {
4123  QCString n = name.mid(i,l);
4124  if (n==arg->name)
4125  {
4126  if (templateNames->find(n)==0)
4127  {
4128  templateNames->insert(n,new int(count));
4129  }
4130  }
4131  p=i+l;
4132  }
4133  }
4134  }
4135  return templateNames;
4136 }
4137 
4141 static ClassDef *findClassWithinClassContext(Definition *context,ClassDef *cd,const QCString &name)
4142 {
4143  ClassDef *result=0;
4144  if (cd==0)
4145  {
4146  return result;
4147  }
4148  FileDef *fd=cd->getFileDef();
4149  if (context && cd!=context)
4150  {
4151  result = getResolvedClass(context,0,name,0,0,TRUE,TRUE);
4152  }
4153  if (result==0)
4154  {
4155  result = getResolvedClass(cd,fd,name,0,0,TRUE,TRUE);
4156  }
4157  if (result==0) // try direct class, needed for namespaced classes imported via tag files (see bug624095)
4158  {
4159  result = getClass(name);
4160  }
4161  if (result==0 &&
4162  (cd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_CSharp || cd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Java) &&
4163  name.find('<')!=-1)
4164  {
4165  result = Doxygen::genericsDict->find(name);
4166  }
4167  //printf("** Trying to find %s within context %s class %s result=%s lookup=%p\n",
4168  // name.data(),
4169  // context ? context->name().data() : "<none>",
4170  // cd ? cd->name().data() : "<none>",
4171  // result ? result->name().data() : "<none>",
4172  // Doxygen::classSDict->find(name)
4173  // );
4174  return result;
4175 }
4176 
4177 
4178 static void findUsedClassesForClass(EntryNav *rootNav,
4179  Definition *context,
4180  ClassDef *masterCd,
4181  ClassDef *instanceCd,
4182  bool isArtificial,
4183  ArgumentList *actualArgs=0,
4184  QDict<int> *templateNames=0
4185  )
4186 {
4187  masterCd->visited=TRUE;
4188  ArgumentList *formalArgs = masterCd->templateArguments();
4189  if (masterCd->memberNameInfoSDict())
4190  {
4191  MemberNameInfoSDict::Iterator mnili(*masterCd->memberNameInfoSDict());
4192  MemberNameInfo *mni;
4193  for (;(mni=mnili.current());++mnili)
4194  {
4195  MemberNameInfoIterator mnii(*mni);
4196  MemberInfo *mi;
4197  for (mnii.toFirst();(mi=mnii.current());++mnii)
4198  {
4199  MemberDef *md=mi->memberDef;
4200  if (md->isVariable() || md->isObjCProperty()) // for each member variable in this class
4201  {
4202  //printf(" Found variable %s in class %s\n",md->name().data(),masterCd->name().data());
4203  QCString type = normalizeNonTemplateArgumentsInString(md->typeString(),masterCd,formalArgs);
4204  QCString typedefValue = resolveTypeDef(masterCd,type);
4205  if (!typedefValue.isEmpty())
4206  {
4207  type = typedefValue;
4208  }
4209  int pos=0;
4210  QCString usedClassName;
4211  QCString templSpec;
4212  bool found=FALSE;
4213  // the type can contain template variables, replace them if present
4214  if (actualArgs)
4215  {
4216  type = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(type,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4217  }
4218 
4219  //printf(" template substitution gives=%s\n",type.data());
4220  while (!found && extractClassNameFromType(type,pos,usedClassName,templSpec,rootNav->lang())!=-1)
4221  {
4222  // find the type (if any) that matches usedClassName
4223  ClassDef *typeCd = getResolvedClass(masterCd,
4224  masterCd->getFileDef(),
4225  usedClassName,
4226  0,0,
4227  FALSE,TRUE
4228  );
4229  //printf("====> usedClassName=%s -> typeCd=%s\n",
4230  // usedClassName.data(),typeCd?typeCd->name().data():"<none>");
4231  if (typeCd)
4232  {
4233  usedClassName = typeCd->name();
4234  }
4235 
4236  int sp=usedClassName.find('<');
4237  if (sp==-1) sp=0;
4238  int si=usedClassName.findRev("::",sp);
4239  if (si!=-1)
4240  {
4241  // replace any namespace aliases
4242  replaceNamespaceAliases(usedClassName,si);
4243  }
4244  // add any template arguments to the class
4245  QCString usedName = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(usedClassName+templSpec);
4246  //printf(" usedName=%s\n",usedName.data());
4247 
4248  bool delTempNames=FALSE;
4249  if (templateNames==0)
4250  {
4251  templateNames = getTemplateArgumentsInName(formalArgs,usedName);
4252  delTempNames=TRUE;
4253  }
4254  BaseInfo bi(usedName,Public,Normal);
4255  findClassRelation(rootNav,context,instanceCd,&bi,templateNames,TemplateInstances,isArtificial);
4256 
4257  if (masterCd->templateArguments())
4258  {
4259  ArgumentListIterator ali(*masterCd->templateArguments());
4260  Argument *arg;
4261  int count=0;
4262  for (ali.toFirst();(arg=ali.current());++ali,++count)
4263  {
4264  if (arg->name==usedName) // type is a template argument
4265  {
4266  found=TRUE;
4267  Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," New used class `%s'\n", qPrint(usedName));
4268 
4269  ClassDef *usedCd = Doxygen::hiddenClasses->find(usedName);
4270  if (usedCd==0)
4271  {
4272  usedCd = new ClassDef(
4273  masterCd->getDefFileName(),masterCd->getDefLine(),
4274  masterCd->getDefColumn(),
4275  usedName,
4276  ClassDef::Class);
4277  //printf("making %s a template argument!!!\n",usedCd->name().data());
4278  usedCd->makeTemplateArgument();
4279  usedCd->setUsedOnly(TRUE);
4280  usedCd->setLanguage(masterCd->getLanguage());
4281  Doxygen::hiddenClasses->append(usedName,usedCd);
4282  }
4283  if (isArtificial) usedCd->setArtificial(TRUE);
4284  Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," Adding used class `%s' (1)\n", qPrint(usedCd->name()));
4285  instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4286  usedCd->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4287  }
4288  }
4289  }
4290 
4291  if (!found)
4292  {
4293  ClassDef *usedCd=findClassWithinClassContext(context,masterCd,usedName);
4294  //printf("Looking for used class %s: result=%s master=%s\n",
4295  // usedName.data(),usedCd?usedCd->name().data():"<none>",masterCd?masterCd->name().data():"<none>");
4296 
4297  if (usedCd)
4298  {
4299  found=TRUE;
4300  Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," Adding used class `%s' (2)\n", qPrint(usedCd->name()));
4301  instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection()); // class exists
4302  usedCd->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4303  }
4304  }
4305  if (delTempNames)
4306  {
4307  delete templateNames;
4308  templateNames=0;
4309  }
4310  }
4311  if (!found && !type.isEmpty()) // used class is not documented in any scope
4312  {
4313  ClassDef *usedCd = Doxygen::hiddenClasses->find(type);
4314  if (usedCd==0 && !Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS))
4315  {
4316  if (type.right(2)=="(*" || type.right(2)=="(^") // type is a function pointer
4317  {
4318  type+=md->argsString();
4319  }
4320  Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," New undocumented used class `%s'\n", qPrint(type));
4321  usedCd = new ClassDef(
4322  masterCd->getDefFileName(),masterCd->getDefLine(),
4323  masterCd->getDefColumn(),
4324  type,ClassDef::Class);
4325  usedCd->setUsedOnly(TRUE);
4326  usedCd->setLanguage(masterCd->getLanguage());
4327  Doxygen::hiddenClasses->append(type,usedCd);
4328  }
4329  if (usedCd)
4330  {
4331  if (isArtificial) usedCd->setArtificial(TRUE);
4332  Debug::print(Debug::Classes,0," Adding used class `%s' (3)\n", qPrint(usedCd->name()));
4333  instanceCd->addUsedClass(usedCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4334  usedCd->addUsedByClass(instanceCd,md->name(),md->protection());
4335  }
4336  }
4337  }
4338  }
4339  }
4340  }
4341  else
4342  {
4343  //printf("no members for class %s (%p)\n",masterCd->name().data(),masterCd);
4344  }
4345 }
4346 
4347 static void findBaseClassesForClass(
4348  EntryNav *rootNav,
4349  Definition *context,
4350  ClassDef *masterCd,
4351  ClassDef *instanceCd,
4352  FindBaseClassRelation_Mode mode,
4353  bool isArtificial,
4354  ArgumentList *actualArgs=0,
4355  QDict<int> *templateNames=0
4356  )
4357 {
4358  Entry *root = rootNav->entry();
4359  //if (masterCd->visited) return;
4360  masterCd->visited=TRUE;
4361  // The base class could ofcouse also be a non-nested class
4362  ArgumentList *formalArgs = masterCd->templateArguments();
4363  QListIterator<BaseInfo> bii(*root->extends);
4364  BaseInfo *bi=0;
4365  for (bii.toFirst();(bi=bii.current());++bii)
4366  {
4367  //printf("masterCd=%s bi->name='%s' #actualArgs=%d\n",
4368  // masterCd->localName().data(),bi->name.data(),actualArgs?(int)actualArgs->count():-1);
4369  bool delTempNames=FALSE;
4370  if (templateNames==0)
4371  {
4372  templateNames = getTemplateArgumentsInName(formalArgs,bi->name);
4373  delTempNames=TRUE;
4374  }
4375  BaseInfo tbi(bi->name,bi->prot,bi->virt);
4376  if (actualArgs) // substitute the formal template arguments of the base class
4377  {
4378  tbi.name = substituteTemplateArgumentsInString(bi->name,formalArgs,actualArgs);
4379  }
4380  //printf("bi->name=%s tbi.name=%s\n",bi->name.data(),tbi.name.data());
4381 
4382  if (mode==DocumentedOnly)
4383  {
4384  // find a documented base class in the correct scope
4385  if (!findClassRelation(rootNav,context,instanceCd,&tbi,templateNames,DocumentedOnly,isArtificial))
4386  {
4387  // 1.8.2: decided to show inheritance relations even if not documented,
4388  // we do make them artificial, so they do not appear in the index
4389  //if (!Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS))
4390  bool b = Config_getBool(HIDE_UNDOC_RELATIONS) ? TRUE : isArtificial;
4391  //{
4392  // no documented base class -> try to find an undocumented one
4393  findClassRelation(rootNav,context,instanceCd,&tbi,templateNames,Undocumented,b);
4394  //}
4395  }
4396  }
4397  else if (mode==TemplateInstances)
4398  {
4399  findClassRelation(rootNav,context,instanceCd,&tbi,templateNames,TemplateInstances,isArtificial);
4400  }
4401  if (delTempNames)
4402  {
4403  delete templateNames;
4404  templateNames=0;
4405  }
4406  }
4407 }
