9307 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9308 
9309 static ParserInterface *getParserForFile(const char *fn)
9310 {
9311  QCString fileName=fn;
9312  QCString extension;
9313  int sep = fileName.findRev('/');
9314  int ei = fileName.findRev('.');
9315  if (ei!=-1 && (sep==-1 || ei>sep)) // matches dir/file.ext but not dir.1/file
9316  {
9317  extension=fileName.right(fileName.length()-ei);
9318  }
9319  else
9320  {
9321  extension = ".no_extension";
9322  }
9323 
9324  return Doxygen::parserManager->getParser(extension);
9325 }
9326 
9327 static void parseFile(ParserInterface *parser,
9328  Entry *root,EntryNav *rootNav,FileDef *fd,const char *fn,
9329  bool sameTu,QStrList &filesInSameTu)
9330 {
9331 #if USE_LIBCLANG
9332  static bool clangAssistedParsing = Config_getBool(CLANG_ASSISTED_PARSING);
9333 #else
9334  static bool clangAssistedParsing = FALSE;
9335 #endif
9336  QCString fileName=fn;
9337  QCString extension;
9338  int ei = fileName.findRev('.');
9339  if (ei!=-1)
9340  {
9341  extension=fileName.right(fileName.length()-ei);
9342  }
9343  else
9344  {
9345  extension = ".no_extension";
9346  }
9347 
9348  QFileInfo fi(fileName);
9349  BufStr preBuf(fi.size()+4096);
9350 
9351  if (Config_getBool(ENABLE_PREPROCESSING) &&
9352  parser->needsPreprocessing(extension))
9353  {
9354  BufStr inBuf(fi.size()+4096);
9355  msg("Preprocessing %s...\n",fn);
9356  readInputFile(fileName,inBuf);
9357  preprocessFile(fileName,inBuf,preBuf);
9358  }
9359  else // no preprocessing
9360  {
9361  msg("Reading %s...\n",fn);
9362  readInputFile(fileName,preBuf);
9363  }
9364  if (preBuf.data() && preBuf.curPos()>0 && *(preBuf.data()+preBuf.curPos()-1)!='\n')
9365  {
9366  preBuf.addChar('\n'); // add extra newline to help parser
9367  }
9368 
9369  BufStr convBuf(preBuf.curPos()+1024);
9370 
9371  // convert multi-line C++ comments to C style comments
9372  convertCppComments(&preBuf,&convBuf,fileName);
9373 
9374  convBuf.addChar('\0');
9375 
9376  if (clangAssistedParsing && !sameTu)
9377  {
9378  fd->getAllIncludeFilesRecursively(filesInSameTu);
9379  }
9380 
9381  // use language parse to parse the file
9382  parser->parseInput(fileName,convBuf.data(),root,sameTu,filesInSameTu);
9383 
9384  // store the Entry tree in a file and create an index to
9385  // navigate/load entries
9386  //printf("root->createNavigationIndex for %s\n",fd->name().data());
9387  root->createNavigationIndex(rootNav,g_storage,fd);
9388 }
9389 
9391 static void parseFiles(Entry *root,EntryNav *rootNav)
9392 {
9393 #if USE_LIBCLANG
9394  static bool clangAssistedParsing = Config_getBool(CLANG_ASSISTED_PARSING);
9395  if (clangAssistedParsing)
9396  {
9397  QDict<void> g_processedFiles(10007);
9398 
9399  // create a dictionary with files to process
9400  QDict<void> g_filesToProcess(10007);
9401  StringListIterator it(g_inputFiles);
9402  QCString *s;
9403  for (;(s=it.current());++it)
9404  {
9405  g_filesToProcess.insert(*s,(void*)0x8);
9406  }
9407 
9408  // process source files (and their include dependencies)
9409  for (it.toFirst();(s=it.current());++it)
9410  {
9411  bool ambig;
9412  FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,s->data(),ambig);
9413  ASSERT(fd!=0);
9414  if (fd->isSource() && !fd->isReference()) // this is a source file
9415  {
9416  QStrList filesInSameTu;
9417  ParserInterface * parser = getParserForFile(s->data());
9418  parser->startTranslationUnit(s->data());
9419  parseFile(parser,root,rootNav,fd,s->data(),FALSE,filesInSameTu);
9420  //printf(" got %d extra files in tu\n",filesInSameTu.count());
9421 
9422  // Now process any include files in the same translation unit
9423  // first. When libclang is used this is much more efficient.
9424  char *incFile = filesInSameTu.first();
9425  while (incFile && g_filesToProcess.find(incFile))
9426  {
9427  if (qstrcmp(incFile,s->data()) && !g_processedFiles.find(incFile))
9428  {
9429  FileDef *ifd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,incFile,ambig);
9430  if (ifd && !ifd->isReference())
9431  {
9432  QStrList moreFiles;
9433  //printf(" Processing %s in same translation unit as %s\n",incFile,s->data());
9434  parseFile(parser,root,rootNav,ifd,incFile,TRUE,moreFiles);
9435  g_processedFiles.insert(incFile,(void*)0x8);
9436  }
9437  }
9438  incFile = filesInSameTu.next();
9439  }
9440  parser->finishTranslationUnit();
9441  g_processedFiles.insert(*s,(void*)0x8);
9442  }
9443  }
9444  // process remaining files
9445  for (it.toFirst();(s=it.current());++it)
9446  {
9447  if (!g_processedFiles.find(*s)) // not yet processed
9448  {
9449  bool ambig;
9450  QStrList filesInSameTu;
9451  FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,s->data(),ambig);
9452  ASSERT(fd!=0);
9453  ParserInterface * parser = getParserForFile(s->data());
9454  parser->startTranslationUnit(s->data());
9455  parseFile(parser,root,rootNav,fd,s->data(),FALSE,filesInSameTu);
9456  parser->finishTranslationUnit();
9457  g_processedFiles.insert(*s,(void*)0x8);
9458  }
9459  }
9460  }
9461  else // normal pocessing
9462 #endif
9463  {
9464  StringListIterator it(g_inputFiles);
9465  QCString *s;
9466  for (;(s=it.current());++it)
9467  {
9468  bool ambig;
9469  QStrList filesInSameTu;
9470  FileDef *fd=findFileDef(Doxygen::inputNameDict,s->data(),ambig);
9471  ASSERT(fd!=0);
9472  ParserInterface * parser = getParserForFile(s->data());
9473  parser->startTranslationUnit(s->data());
9474  parseFile(parser,root,rootNav,fd,s->data(),FALSE,filesInSameTu);
9475  }
9476  }
9477 }
9478 
9479 // resolves a path that may include symlinks, if a recursive symlink is
9480 // found an empty string is returned.
9481 static QCString resolveSymlink(QCString path)
9482 {
9483  int sepPos=0;
9484  int oldPos=0;
9485  QFileInfo fi;
9486  QDict<void> nonSymlinks;
9487  QDict<void> known;
9488  QCString result = path;
9489  QCString oldPrefix = "/";
9490  do
9491  {
9492 #ifdef WIN32
9493  // UNC path, skip server and share name
9494  if (sepPos==0 && (result.left(2)=="//" || result.left(2)=="\\\\"))
9495  sepPos = result.find('/',2);
9496  if (sepPos!=-1)
9497  sepPos = result.find('/',sepPos+1);
9498 #else
9499  sepPos = result.find('/',sepPos+1);
9500 #endif
9501  QCString prefix = sepPos==-1 ? result : result.left(sepPos);
9502  if (nonSymlinks.find(prefix)==0)
9503  {
9504  fi.setFile(prefix);
9505  if (fi.isSymLink())
9506  {
9507  QString target = fi.readLink();
9508  bool isRelative = QFileInfo(target).isRelative();
9509  if (isRelative)
9510  {
9511  target = QDir::cleanDirPath(oldPrefix+"/"+target.data());
9512  }
9513  if (sepPos!=-1)
9514  {
9515  if (fi.isDir() && target.length()>0 && target.at(target.length()-1)!='/')
9516  {
9517  target+='/';
9518  }
9519  target+=result.mid(sepPos);
9520  }
9521  result = QDir::cleanDirPath(target).data();
9522  sepPos = 0;
9523  if (known.find(result)) return QCString(); // recursive symlink!
9524  known.insert(result,(void*)0x8);
9525  if (isRelative)
9526  {
9527  sepPos = oldPos;
9528  }
9529  else // link to absolute path
9530  {
9531  sepPos = 0;
9532  oldPrefix = "/";
9533  }
9534  }
9535  else
9536  {
9537  nonSymlinks.insert(prefix,(void*)0x8);
9538  oldPrefix = prefix;
9539  }
9540  oldPos = sepPos;
9541  }
9542  }
9543  while (sepPos!=-1);
9544  return QDir::cleanDirPath(result).data();
9545 }
9546 
9547 static QDict<void> g_pathsVisited(1009);
9548 
9549 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9550 // Read all files matching at least one pattern in `patList' in the
9551 // directory represented by `fi'.
9552 // The directory is read iff the recusiveFlag is set.
9553 // The contents of all files is append to the input string
9554 
9555 int readDir(QFileInfo *fi,
9556  FileNameList *fnList,
9557  FileNameDict *fnDict,
9558  StringDict *exclDict,
9559  QStrList *patList,
9560  QStrList *exclPatList,
9561  StringList *resultList,
9562  StringDict *resultDict,
9563  bool errorIfNotExist,
9564  bool recursive,
9565  QDict<void> *killDict,
9566  QDict<void> *paths
9567  )
9568 {
9569  QCString dirName = fi->absFilePath().utf8();
9570  if (paths && paths->find(dirName)==0)
9571  {
9572  paths->insert(dirName,(void*)0x8);
9573  }
9574  if (fi->isSymLink())
9575  {
9576  dirName = resolveSymlink(dirName.data());
9577  if (dirName.isEmpty()) return 0; // recusive symlink
9578  if (g_pathsVisited.find(dirName)) return 0; // already visited path
9579  g_pathsVisited.insert(dirName,(void*)0x8);
9580  }
9581  QDir dir(dirName);
9582  dir.setFilter( QDir::Files | QDir::Dirs | QDir::Hidden );
9583  int totalSize=0;
9584  msg("Searching for files in directory %s\n", fi->absFilePath().data());
9585  //printf("killDict=%p count=%d\n",killDict,killDict->count());
9586 
9587  const QFileInfoList *list = dir.entryInfoList();
9588  if (list)
9589  {
9590  QFileInfoListIterator it( *list );
9591  QFileInfo *cfi;
9592 
9593  while ((cfi=it.current()))
9594  {
9595  if (exclDict==0 || exclDict->find(cfi->absFilePath().utf8())==0)
9596  { // file should not be excluded
9597  //printf("killDict->find(%s)\n",cfi->absFilePath().data());
9598  if (!cfi->exists() || !cfi->isReadable())
9599  {
9600  if (errorIfNotExist)
9601  {
9602  warn_uncond("source %s is not a readable file or directory... skipping.\n",cfi->absFilePath().data());
9603  }
9604  }
9605  else if (cfi->isFile() &&
9606  (!Config_getBool(EXCLUDE_SYMLINKS) || !cfi->isSymLink()) &&
9607  (patList==0 || patternMatch(*cfi,patList)) &&
9608  !patternMatch(*cfi,exclPatList) &&
9609  (killDict==0 || killDict->find(cfi->absFilePath().utf8())==0)
9610  )
9611  {
9612  totalSize+=cfi->size()+cfi->absFilePath().length()+4;
9613  QCString name=cfi->fileName().utf8();
9614  //printf("New file %s\n",name.data());
9615  if (fnDict)
9616  {
9617  FileDef *fd=new FileDef(cfi->dirPath().utf8()+"/",name);
9618  FileName *fn=0;
9619  if (!name.isEmpty() && (fn=(*fnDict)[name]))
9620  {
9621  fn->append(fd);
9622  }
9623  else
9624  {
9625  fn = new FileName(cfi->absFilePath().utf8(),name);
9626  fn->append(fd);
9627  if (fnList) fnList->inSort(fn);
9628  fnDict->insert(name,fn);
9629  }
9630  }
9631  QCString *rs=0;
9632  if (resultList || resultDict)
9633  {
9634  rs=new QCString(cfi->absFilePath().utf8());
9635  }
9636  if (resultList) resultList->append(rs);
9637  if (resultDict) resultDict->insert(cfi->absFilePath().utf8(),rs);
9638  if (killDict) killDict->insert(cfi->absFilePath().utf8(),(void *)0x8);
9639  }
9640  else if (recursive &&
9641  (!Config_getBool(EXCLUDE_SYMLINKS) || !cfi->isSymLink()) &&
9642  cfi->isDir() &&
9643  !patternMatch(*cfi,exclPatList) &&
9644  cfi->fileName().at(0)!='.') // skip "." ".." and ".dir"
9645  {
9646  cfi->setFile(cfi->absFilePath());
9647  totalSize+=readDir(cfi,fnList,fnDict,exclDict,
9648  patList,exclPatList,resultList,resultDict,errorIfNotExist,
9649  recursive,killDict,paths);
9650  }
9651  }
9652  ++it;
9653  }
9654  }
9655  return totalSize;
9656 }
9657 
9658 
9659 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9660 // read a file or all files in a directory and append their contents to the
9661 // input string. The names of the files are appended to the `fiList' list.
9662 
9663 int readFileOrDirectory(const char *s,
9664  FileNameList *fnList,
9665  FileNameDict *fnDict,
9666  StringDict *exclDict,
9667  QStrList *patList,
9668  QStrList *exclPatList,
9669  StringList *resultList,
9670  StringDict *resultDict,
9671  bool recursive,
9672  bool errorIfNotExist,
9673  QDict<void> *killDict,
9674  QDict<void> *paths
9675  )
9676 {
9677  //printf("killDict=%p count=%d\n",killDict,killDict->count());
9678  // strip trailing slashes
9679  if (s==0) return 0;
9680  QCString fs = s;
9681  char lc = fs.at(fs.length()-1);
9682  if (lc=='/' || lc=='\\') fs = fs.left(fs.length()-1);
9683 
9684  QFileInfo fi(fs);
9685  //printf("readFileOrDirectory(%s)\n",s);
9686  int totalSize=0;
9687  {
9688  if (exclDict==0 || exclDict->find(fi.absFilePath().utf8())==0)
9689  {
9690  if (!fi.exists() || !fi.isReadable())
9691  {
9692  if (errorIfNotExist)
9693  {
9694  warn_uncond("source %s is not a readable file or directory... skipping.\n",s);
9695  }
9696  }
9697  else if (!Config_getBool(EXCLUDE_SYMLINKS) || !fi.isSymLink())
9698  {
9699  if (fi.isFile())
9700  {
9701  QCString dirPath = fi.dirPath(TRUE).utf8();
9702  QCString filePath = fi.absFilePath().utf8();
9703  if (paths && paths->find(dirPath))
9704  {
9705  paths->insert(dirPath,(void*)0x8);
9706  }
9707  //printf("killDict->find(%s)\n",fi.absFilePath().data());
9708  if (killDict==0 || killDict->find(filePath)==0)
9709  {
9710  totalSize+=fi.size()+fi.absFilePath().length()+4; //readFile(&fi,fiList,input);
9711  //fiList->inSort(new FileInfo(fi));
9712  QCString name=fi.fileName().utf8();
9713  //printf("New file %s\n",name.data());
9714  if (fnDict)
9715  {
9716  FileDef *fd=new FileDef(dirPath+"/",name);
9717  FileName *fn=0;
9718  if (!name.isEmpty() && (fn=(*fnDict)[name]))
9719  {
9720  fn->append(fd);
9721  }
9722  else
9723  {
9724  fn = new FileName(filePath,name);
9725  fn->append(fd);
9726  if (fnList) fnList->inSort(fn);
9727  fnDict->insert(name,fn);
9728  }
9729  }
9730  QCString *rs=0;
9731  if (resultList || resultDict)
9732  {
9733  rs=new QCString(filePath);
9734  if (resultList) resultList->append(rs);
9735  if (resultDict) resultDict->insert(filePath,rs);
9736  }
9737 
9738  if (killDict) killDict->insert(fi.absFilePath().utf8(),(void *)0x8);
9739  }
9740  }
9741  else if (fi.isDir()) // readable dir
9742  {
9743  totalSize+=readDir(&fi,fnList,fnDict,exclDict,patList,
9744  exclPatList,resultList,resultDict,errorIfNotExist,
9745  recursive,killDict,paths);
9746  }
9747  }
9748  }
9749  }
9750  return totalSize;
9751 }

9753 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9754 
9755 void readFormulaRepository()
9756 {
9757  QFile f(Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT)+"/formula.repository");
9758  if (f.open(IO_ReadOnly)) // open repository
9759  {
9760  msg("Reading formula repository...\n");
9761  QTextStream t(&f);
9762  QCString line;
9763  while (!t.eof())
9764  {
9765  line=t.readLine().utf8();
9766  int se=line.find(':'); // find name and text separator.
9767  if (se==-1)
9768  {
9769  warn_uncond("formula.repository is corrupted!\n");
9770  break;
9771  }
9772  else
9773  {
9774  QCString formName = line.left(se);
9775  QCString formText = line.right(line.length()-se-1);
9776  Formula *f=new Formula(formText);
9777  Doxygen::formulaList->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
9778  Doxygen::formulaList->append(f);
9779  Doxygen::formulaDict->insert(formText,f);
9780  Doxygen::formulaNameDict->insert(formName,f);
9781  }
9782  }
9783  }
9784 }

9786 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9787 
9788 static void expandAliases()
9789 {
9790  QDictIterator<QCString> adi(Doxygen::aliasDict);
9791  QCString *s;
9792  for (adi.toFirst();(s=adi.current());++adi)
9793  {
9794  *s = expandAlias(adi.currentKey(),*s);
9795  }
9796 }
9797 
9798 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9799 
9800 static void escapeAliases()
9801 {
9802  QDictIterator<QCString> adi(Doxygen::aliasDict);
9803  QCString *s;
9804  for (adi.toFirst();(s=adi.current());++adi)
9805  {
9806  QCString value=*s,newValue;
9807  int in,p=0;
9808  // for each \n in the alias command value
9809  while ((in=value.find("\\n",p))!=-1)
9810  {
9811  newValue+=value.mid(p,in-p);
9812  // expand \n's except if \n is part of a built-in command.
9813  if (value.mid(in,5)!="\\note" &&
9814  value.mid(in,5)!="\\name" &&
9815  value.mid(in,10)!="\\namespace" &&
9816  value.mid(in,14)!="\\nosubgrouping"
9817  )
9818  {
9819  newValue+="\\_linebr ";
9820  }
9821  else
9822  {
9823  newValue+="\\n";
9824  }
9825  p=in+2;
9826  }
9827  newValue+=value.mid(p,value.length()-p);
9828  *s=newValue;
9829  //printf("Alias %s has value %s\n",adi.currentKey().data(),s->data());
9830  }
9831 }
9832 
9833 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9834 
9835 void readAliases()
9836 {
9837  // add aliases to a dictionary
9838  Doxygen::aliasDict.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
9839  QStrList &aliasList = Config_getList(ALIASES);
9840  const char *s=aliasList.first();
9841  while (s)
9842  {
9843  if (Doxygen::aliasDict[s]==0)
9844  {
9845  QCString alias=s;
9846  int i=alias.find('=');
9847  if (i>0)
9848  {
9849  QCString name=alias.left(i).stripWhiteSpace();
9850  QCString value=alias.right(alias.length()-i-1);
9851  //printf("Alias: found name=`%s' value=`%s'\n",name.data(),value.data());
9852  if (!name.isEmpty())
9853  {
9854  QCString *dn=Doxygen::aliasDict[name];
9855  if (dn==0) // insert new alias
9856  {
9857  Doxygen::aliasDict.insert(name,new QCString(value));
9858  }
9859  else // overwrite previous alias
9860  {
9861  *dn=value;
9862  }
9863  }
9864  }
9865  }
9866  s=aliasList.next();
9867  }
9868  expandAliases();
9869  escapeAliases();
9870 }
9871 
9872 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9873 
9874 static void dumpSymbol(FTextStream &t,Definition *d)
9875 {
9876  QCString anchor;
9877  if (d->definitionType()==Definition::TypeMember)
9878  {
9879  MemberDef *md = (MemberDef *)d;
9880  anchor=":"+md->anchor();
9881  }
9882  QCString scope;
9883  if (d->getOuterScope() && d->getOuterScope()!=Doxygen::globalScope)
9884  {
9885  scope = d->getOuterScope()->getOutputFileBase()+Doxygen::htmlFileExtension;
9886  }
9887  t << "REPLACE INTO symbols (symbol_id,scope_id,name,file,line) VALUES('"
9888  << d->getOutputFileBase()+Doxygen::htmlFileExtension+anchor << "','"
9889  << scope << "','"
9890  << d->name() << "','"
9891  << d->getDefFileName() << "','"
9892  << d->getDefLine()
9893  << "');" << endl;
9894 }
9895 
9896 static void dumpSymbolMap()
9897 {
9898  QFile f("symbols.sql");
9899  if (f.open(IO_WriteOnly))
9900  {
9901  FTextStream t(&f);
9902  QDictIterator<DefinitionIntf> di(*Doxygen::symbolMap);
9903  DefinitionIntf *intf;
9904  for (;(intf=di.current());++di)
9905  {
9906  if (intf->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeSymbolList) // list of symbols
9907  {
9908  DefinitionListIterator dli(*(DefinitionList*)intf);
9909  Definition *d;
9910  // for each symbol
9911  for (dli.toFirst();(d=dli.current());++dli)
9912  {
9913  dumpSymbol(t,d);
9914  }
9915  }
9916  else // single symbol
9917  {
9918  Definition *d = (Definition *)intf;
9919  if (d!=Doxygen::globalScope) dumpSymbol(t,d);
9920  }
9921  }
9922  }
9923 }

9967 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9968 // read the argument of option `c' from the comment argument list and
9969 // update the option index `optind'.
9970 
9971 static const char *getArg(int argc,char **argv,int &optind)
9972 {
9973  char *s=0;
9974  if (qstrlen(&argv[optind][2])>0)
9975  s=&argv[optind][2];
9976  else if (optind+1<argc && argv[optind+1][0]!='-')
9977  s=argv[++optind];
9978  return s;
9979 }

9981 //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
9982 
9983 void initDoxygen()
9984 {
9985  initResources();
9986  const char *lang = portable_getenv("LC_ALL");

10077 void cleanUpDoxygen()
10078 {
10079  delete Doxygen::sectionDict;
10080  delete Doxygen::formulaNameDict;
10081  delete Doxygen::formulaDict;
10082  delete Doxygen::formulaList;
10083  delete Doxygen::indexList;
10084  delete Doxygen::genericsDict;
10085  delete Doxygen::inputNameDict;
10086  delete Doxygen::includeNameDict;
10087  delete Doxygen::exampleNameDict;
10088  delete Doxygen::imageNameDict;
10089  delete Doxygen::dotFileNameDict;
10090  delete Doxygen::mscFileNameDict;
10091  delete Doxygen::diaFileNameDict;
10092  delete Doxygen::mainPage;
10093  delete Doxygen::pageSDict;
10094  delete Doxygen::exampleSDict;
10095  delete Doxygen::globalScope;
10096  delete Doxygen::xrefLists;
10097  delete Doxygen::parserManager;
10098  cleanUpPreprocessor();
10099  delete theTranslator;
10100  delete g_outputList;
10101  Mappers::freeMappers();
10102  codeFreeScanner();
10103 
10104  if (Doxygen::symbolMap)
10105  {
10106  // iterate through Doxygen::symbolMap and delete all
10107  // DefinitionList objects, since they have no owner
10108  QDictIterator<DefinitionIntf> dli(*Doxygen::symbolMap);
10109  DefinitionIntf *di;
10110  for (dli.toFirst();(di=dli.current());)
10111  {
10112  if (di->definitionType()==DefinitionIntf::TypeSymbolList)
10113  {
10114  DefinitionIntf *tmp = Doxygen::symbolMap->take(dli.currentKey());
10115  delete (DefinitionList *)tmp;
10116  }
10117  else
10118  {
10119  ++dli;
10120  }
10121  }
10122  }
10123 
10124  delete Doxygen::inputNameList;
10125  delete Doxygen::memberNameSDict;
10126  delete Doxygen::functionNameSDict;
10127  delete Doxygen::groupSDict;
10128  delete Doxygen::classSDict;
10129  delete Doxygen::hiddenClasses;
10130  delete Doxygen::namespaceSDict;
10131  delete Doxygen::directories;
10132 
10133  //delete Doxygen::symbolMap; <- we cannot do this unless all static lists
10134  // (such as Doxygen::namespaceSDict)
10135  // with objects based on Definition are made
10136  // dynamic first
10137 }

10139 static int computeIdealCacheParam(uint v)
10140 {
10141  //printf("computeIdealCacheParam(v=%u)\n",v);
10142 
10143  int r=0;
10144  while (v!=0) v>>=1,r++;
10145  // r = log2(v)
10146 
10147  // convert to a valid cache size value
10148  return QMAX(0,QMIN(r-16,9));
10149 }

10151 void readConfiguration(int argc, char **argv)
10152 {
10153  /**************************************************************************
10154  * Handle arguments *
10155  **************************************************************************/
10156 
10157  int optind=1;
10158  const char *configName=0;
10159  const char *layoutName=0;
10160  const char *debugLabel;
10161  const char *formatName;
10162  bool genConfig=FALSE;
10163  bool shortList=FALSE;
10164  bool updateConfig=FALSE;
10165  bool genLayout=FALSE;
10166  int retVal;
10167  while (optind<argc && argv[optind][0]=='-' &&
10168  (isalpha(argv[optind][1]) || argv[optind][1]=='?' ||
10169  argv[optind][1]=='-')
10170  )
10171  {
10172  switch(argv[optind][1])
10173  {
10174  case 'g':
10175  genConfig=TRUE;
10176  configName=getArg(argc,argv,optind);
10177  if (optind+1<argc && qstrcmp(argv[optind+1],"-")==0)
10178  { configName="-"; optind++; }
10179  if (!configName)
10180  { configName="Doxyfile"; }
10181  break;
10182  case 'l':
10183  genLayout=TRUE;
10184  layoutName=getArg(argc,argv,optind);
10185  if (!layoutName)
10186  { layoutName="DoxygenLayout.xml"; }
10187  break;
10188  case 'd':
10189  debugLabel=getArg(argc,argv,optind);
10190  if (!debugLabel)
10191  {
10192  err("option \"-d\" is missing debug specifier.\n");
10193  devUsage();
10194  cleanUpDoxygen();
10195  exit(1);
10196  }
10197  retVal = Debug::setFlag(debugLabel);
10198  if (!retVal)
10199  {
10200  err("option \"-d\" has unknown debug specifier: \"%s\".\n",debugLabel);
10201  cleanUpDoxygen();
10202  exit(1);
10203  }
10204  break;
10205  case 's':
10206  shortList=TRUE;
10207  break;
10208  case 'u':
10209  updateConfig=TRUE;
10210  break;
10211  case 'e':
10212  formatName=getArg(argc,argv,optind);
10213  if (!formatName)
10214  {
10215  err("option \"-e\" is missing format specifier rtf.\n");
10216  cleanUpDoxygen();
10217  exit(1);
10218  }
10219  if (qstricmp(formatName,"rtf")==0)
10220  {
10221  if (optind+1>=argc)
10222  {
10223  err("option \"-e rtf\" is missing an extensions file name\n");
10224  cleanUpDoxygen();
10225  exit(1);
10226  }
10227  QFile f;
10228  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+1],f))
10229  {
10230  RTFGenerator::writeExtensionsFile(f);
10231  }
10232  cleanUpDoxygen();
10233  exit(0);
10234  }
10235  err("option \"-e\" has invalid format specifier.\n");
10236  cleanUpDoxygen();
10237  exit(1);
10238  break;
10239  case 'w':
10240  formatName=getArg(argc,argv,optind);
10241  if (!formatName)
10242  {
10243  err("option \"-w\" is missing format specifier rtf, html or latex\n");
10244  cleanUpDoxygen();
10245  exit(1);
10246  }
10247  if (qstricmp(formatName,"rtf")==0)
10248  {
10249  if (optind+1>=argc)
10250  {
10251  err("option \"-w rtf\" is missing a style sheet file name\n");
10252  cleanUpDoxygen();
10253  exit(1);
10254  }
10255  QFile f;
10256  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+1],f))
10257  {
10258  RTFGenerator::writeStyleSheetFile(f);
10259  }
10260  cleanUpDoxygen();
10261  exit(1);
10262  }
10263  else if (qstricmp(formatName,"html")==0)
10264  {
10265  Config::init();
10266  if (optind+4<argc || QFileInfo("Doxyfile").exists())
10267  // explicit config file mentioned or default found on disk
10268  {
10269  QCString df = optind+4<argc ? argv[optind+4] : QCString("Doxyfile");
10270  if (!Config::parse(df)) // parse the config file
10271  {
10272  err("error opening or reading configuration file %s!\n",argv[optind+4]);
10273  cleanUpDoxygen();
10274  exit(1);
10275  }
10276  }
10277  if (optind+3>=argc)
10278  {
10279  err("option \"-w html\" does not have enough arguments\n");
10280  cleanUpDoxygen();
10281  exit(1);
10282  }
10283  Config::postProcess(TRUE);
10284  Config::checkAndCorrect();
10285 
10286  QCString outputLanguage=Config_getEnum(OUTPUT_LANGUAGE);
10287  if (!setTranslator(outputLanguage))
10288  {
10289  warn_uncond("Output language %s not supported! Using English instead.\n", outputLanguage.data());
10290  }
10291 
10292  QFile f;
10293  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+1],f))
10294  {
10295  HtmlGenerator::writeHeaderFile(f, argv[optind+3]);
10296  }
10297  f.close();
10298  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+2],f))
10299  {
10300  HtmlGenerator::writeFooterFile(f);
10301  }
10302  f.close();
10303  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+3],f))
10304  {
10305  HtmlGenerator::writeStyleSheetFile(f);
10306  }
10307  cleanUpDoxygen();
10308  exit(0);
10309  }
10310  else if (qstricmp(formatName,"latex")==0)
10311  {
10312  Config::init();
10313  if (optind+4<argc || QFileInfo("Doxyfile").exists())
10314  {
10315  QCString df = optind+4<argc ? argv[optind+4] : QCString("Doxyfile");
10316  if (!Config::parse(df))
10317  {
10318  err("error opening or reading configuration file %s!\n",argv[optind+4]);
10319  cleanUpDoxygen();
10320  exit(1);
10321  }
10322  }
10323  if (optind+3>=argc)
10324  {
10325  err("option \"-w latex\" does not have enough arguments\n");
10326  cleanUpDoxygen();
10327  exit(1);
10328  }
10329  Config::postProcess(TRUE);
10330  Config::checkAndCorrect();
10331 
10332  QCString outputLanguage=Config_getEnum(OUTPUT_LANGUAGE);
10333  if (!setTranslator(outputLanguage))
10334  {
10335  warn_uncond("Output language %s not supported! Using English instead.\n", outputLanguage.data());
10336  }
10337 
10338  QFile f;
10339  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+1],f))
10340  {
10341  LatexGenerator::writeHeaderFile(f);
10342  }
10343  f.close();
10344  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+2],f))
10345  {
10346  LatexGenerator::writeFooterFile(f);
10347  }
10348  f.close();
10349  if (openOutputFile(argv[optind+3],f))
10350  {
10351  LatexGenerator::writeStyleSheetFile(f);
10352  }
10353  cleanUpDoxygen();
10354  exit(0);
10355  }
10356  else
10357  {
10358  err("Illegal format specifier \"%s\": should be one of rtf, html or latex\n",formatName);
10359  cleanUpDoxygen();
10360  exit(1);
10361  }
10362  break;
10363  case 'm':
10364  g_dumpSymbolMap = TRUE;
10365  break;
10366  case 'v':
10367  msg("%s\n",versionString);
10368  cleanUpDoxygen();
10369  exit(0);
10370  break;
10371  case '-':
10372  if (qstrcmp(&argv[optind][2],"help")==0)
10373  {
10374  usage(argv[0]);
10375  exit(0);
10376  }
10377  else if (qstrcmp(&argv[optind][2],"version")==0)
10378  {
10379  msg("%s\n",versionString);
10380  cleanUpDoxygen();
10381  exit(0);
10382  }
10383  else
10384  {
10385  err("Unknown option \"-%s\"\n",&argv[optind][1]);
10386  usage(argv[0]);
10387  exit(1);
10388  }
10389  break;
10390  case 'b':
10391  setvbuf(stdout,NULL,_IONBF,0);
10392  Doxygen::outputToWizard=TRUE;
10393  break;
10394  case 'T':
10395  msg("Warning: this option activates output generation via Django like template files. "
10396  "This option is scheduled for doxygen 2.0, is currently incomplete and highly experimental! "
10397  "Only use if you are a doxygen developer\n");
10398  g_useOutputTemplate=TRUE;
10399  break;
10400  case 'h':
10401  case '?':
10402  usage(argv[0]);
10403  exit(0);
10404  break;
10405  default:
10406  err("Unknown option \"-%c\"\n",argv[optind][1]);
10407  usage(argv[0]);
10408  exit(1);
10409  }
10410  optind++;
10411  }
10412 
10413  /**************************************************************************
10414  * Parse or generate the config file *
10415  **************************************************************************/
10416 
10417  Config::init();
10418 
10419  if (genConfig && g_useOutputTemplate)
10420  {
10421  generateTemplateFiles("templates");
10422  cleanUpDoxygen();
10423  exit(0);
10424  }
10425 
10426  if (genConfig)
10427  {
10428  generateConfigFile(configName,shortList);
10429  cleanUpDoxygen();
10430  exit(0);
10431  }
10432  if (genLayout)
10433  {
10434  writeDefaultLayoutFile(layoutName);
10435  cleanUpDoxygen();
10436  exit(0);
10437  }
10438 
10439  QFileInfo configFileInfo1("Doxyfile"),configFileInfo2("doxyfile");
10440  if (optind>=argc)
10441  {
10442  if (configFileInfo1.exists())
10443  {
10444  configName="Doxyfile";
10445  }
10446  else if (configFileInfo2.exists())
10447  {
10448  configName="doxyfile";
10449  }
10450  else
10451  {
10452  err("Doxyfile not found and no input file specified!\n");
10453  usage(argv[0]);
10454  exit(1);
10455  }
10456  }
10457  else
10458  {
10459  QFileInfo fi(argv[optind]);
10460  if (fi.exists() || qstrcmp(argv[optind],"-")==0)
10461  {
10462  configName=argv[optind];
10463  }
10464  else
10465  {
10466  err("configuration file %s not found!\n",argv[optind]);
10467  usage(argv[0]);
10468  exit(1);
10469  }
10470  }
10471 
10472 
10473  if (!Config::parse(configName,updateConfig))
10474  {
10475  err("could not open or read configuration file %s!\n",configName);
10476  cleanUpDoxygen();
10477  exit(1);
10478  }
10479 
10480  if (updateConfig)
10481  {
10482  generateConfigFile(configName,shortList,TRUE);
10483  cleanUpDoxygen();
10484  exit(0);
10485  }
10486 
10487  /* Perlmod wants to know the path to the config file.*/
10488  QFileInfo configFileInfo(configName);
10489  setPerlModDoxyfile(configFileInfo.absFilePath().data());
10490 
10491 }

10494 void checkConfiguration()
10495 {
10496 
10497  Config::postProcess(FALSE);
10498  Config::checkAndCorrect();
10499  initWarningFormat();
10500 }

10503 void adjustConfiguration()
10504 {
10505  Doxygen::globalScope = new NamespaceDef("<globalScope>",1,1,"<globalScope>");
10506  Doxygen::inputNameDict = new FileNameDict(10007);
10507  Doxygen::includeNameDict = new FileNameDict(10007);
10508  Doxygen::exampleNameDict = new FileNameDict(1009);
10509  Doxygen::exampleNameDict->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10510  Doxygen::imageNameDict = new FileNameDict(257);
10511  Doxygen::imageNameDict->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10512  Doxygen::dotFileNameDict = new FileNameDict(257);
10513  Doxygen::mscFileNameDict = new FileNameDict(257);
10514  Doxygen::diaFileNameDict = new FileNameDict(257);
10515 
10516  QCString outputLanguage=Config_getEnum(OUTPUT_LANGUAGE);
10517  if (!setTranslator(outputLanguage))
10518  {
10519  warn_uncond("Output language %s not supported! Using English instead.\n",
10520  outputLanguage.data());
10521  }
10522  QStrList &includePath = Config_getList(INCLUDE_PATH);
10523  char *s=includePath.first();
10524  while (s)
10525  {
10526  QFileInfo fi(s);
10527  addSearchDir(fi.absFilePath().utf8());
10528  s=includePath.next();
10529  }
10530 
10531  /* Set the global html file extension. */
10532  Doxygen::htmlFileExtension = Config_getString(HTML_FILE_EXTENSION);
10533 
10534 
10535  Doxygen::xrefLists->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10536 
10537  Doxygen::parseSourcesNeeded = Config_getBool(CALL_GRAPH) ||
10538  Config_getBool(CALLER_GRAPH) ||
10539  Config_getBool(REFERENCES_RELATION) ||
10540  Config_getBool(REFERENCED_BY_RELATION);
10541 
10542  Doxygen::markdownSupport = Config_getBool(MARKDOWN_SUPPORT);
10543 
10544  /**************************************************************************
10545  * Add custom extension mappings
10546  **************************************************************************/
10547 
10548  QStrList &extMaps = Config_getList(EXTENSION_MAPPING);
10549  char *mapping = extMaps.first();
10550  while (mapping)
10551  {
10552  QCString mapStr = mapping;
10553  int i;
10554  if ((i=mapStr.find('='))!=-1)
10555  {
10556  QCString ext=mapStr.left(i).stripWhiteSpace().lower();
10557  QCString language=mapStr.mid(i+1).stripWhiteSpace().lower();
10558  if (!updateLanguageMapping(ext,language))
10559  {
10560  err("Failed to map file extension '%s' to unsupported language '%s'.\n"
10561  "Check the EXTENSION_MAPPING setting in the config file.\n",
10562  ext.data(),language.data());
10563  }
10564  else
10565  {
10566  msg("Adding custom extension mapping: .%s will be treated as language %s\n",
10567  ext.data(),language.data());
10568  }
10569  }
10570  mapping = extMaps.next();
10571  }
10572 
10573 
10574  // add predefined macro name to a dictionary
10575  QStrList &expandAsDefinedList =Config_getList(EXPAND_AS_DEFINED);
10576  s=expandAsDefinedList.first();
10577  while (s)
10578  {
10579  if (Doxygen::expandAsDefinedDict[s]==0)
10580  {
10581  Doxygen::expandAsDefinedDict.insert(s,(void *)666);
10582  }
10583  s=expandAsDefinedList.next();
10584  }
10585 
10586  // read aliases and store them in a dictionary
10587  readAliases();
10588 
10589  // store number of spaces in a tab into Doxygen::spaces
10590  int &tabSize = Config_getInt(TAB_SIZE);
10591  Doxygen::spaces.resize(tabSize+1);
10592  int sp;for (sp=0;sp<tabSize;sp++) Doxygen::spaces.at(sp)=' ';
10593  Doxygen::spaces.at(tabSize)='\0';
10594 }

10596 #ifdef HAS_SIGNALS
10597 static void stopDoxygen(int)
10598 {
10599  QDir thisDir;
10600  msg("Cleaning up...\n");
10601  if (!Doxygen::entryDBFileName.isEmpty())
10602  {
10603  thisDir.remove(Doxygen::entryDBFileName);
10604  }
10605  if (!Doxygen::objDBFileName.isEmpty())
10606  {
10607  thisDir.remove(Doxygen::objDBFileName);
10608  }
10609  killpg(0,SIGINT);
10610  exit(1);
10611 }
10612 #endif
10613 
10614 static void writeTagFile()
10615 {
10616  QCString &generateTagFile = Config_getString(GENERATE_TAGFILE);
10617  if (generateTagFile.isEmpty()) return;
10618 
10619  QFile tag(generateTagFile);
10620  if (!tag.open(IO_WriteOnly))
10621  {
10622  err("cannot open tag file %s for writing\n",
10623  generateTagFile.data()
10624  );
10625  return;
10626  }
10627  FTextStream tagFile(&tag);
10628  tagFile << "<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' standalone='yes' ?>" << endl;
10629  tagFile << "<tagfile>" << endl;
10630 
10631  // for each file
10632  FileNameListIterator fnli(*Doxygen::inputNameList);
10633  FileName *fn;
10634  for (fnli.toFirst();(fn=fnli.current());++fnli)
10635  {
10636  FileNameIterator fni(*fn);
10637  FileDef *fd;
10638  for (fni.toFirst();(fd=fni.current());++fni)
10639  {
10640  if (fd->isLinkableInProject()) fd->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10641  }
10642  }
10643  // for each class
10644  ClassSDict::Iterator cli(*Doxygen::classSDict);
10645  ClassDef *cd;
10646  for ( ; (cd=cli.current()) ; ++cli )
10647  {
10648  if (cd->isLinkableInProject()) cd->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10649  }
10650  // for each namespace
10651  NamespaceSDict::Iterator nli(*Doxygen::namespaceSDict);
10652  NamespaceDef *nd;
10653  for ( ; (nd=nli.current()) ; ++nli )
10654  {
10655  if (nd->isLinkableInProject()) nd->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10656  }
10657  // for each group
10658  GroupSDict::Iterator gli(*Doxygen::groupSDict);
10659  GroupDef *gd;
10660  for (gli.toFirst();(gd=gli.current());++gli)
10661  {
10662  if (gd->isLinkableInProject()) gd->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10663  }
10664  // for each page
10665  PageSDict::Iterator pdi(*Doxygen::pageSDict);
10666  PageDef *pd=0;
10667  for (pdi.toFirst();(pd=pdi.current());++pdi)
10668  {
10669  if (pd->isLinkableInProject()) pd->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10670  }
10671  if (Doxygen::mainPage) Doxygen::mainPage->writeTagFile(tagFile);
10672 
10673  /*
10674  if (Doxygen::mainPage && !Config_getString(GENERATE_TAGFILE).isEmpty())
10675  {
10676  tagFile << " <compound kind=\"page\">" << endl
10677  << " <name>"
10678  << convertToXML(Doxygen::mainPage->name())
10679  << "</name>" << endl
10680  << " <title>"
10681  << convertToXML(Doxygen::mainPage->title())
10682  << "</title>" << endl
10683  << " <filename>"
10684  << convertToXML(Doxygen::mainPage->getOutputFileBase())
10685  << "</filename>" << endl;
10686 
10687  mainPage->writeDocAnchorsToTagFile();
10688  tagFile << " </compound>" << endl;
10689  }
10690  */
10691 
10692  tagFile << "</tagfile>" << endl;
10693 }
10694 
10695 static void exitDoxygen()
10696 {
10697  if (!g_successfulRun) // premature exit
10698  {
10699  QDir thisDir;
10700  msg("Exiting...\n");
10701  if (!Doxygen::entryDBFileName.isEmpty())
10702  {
10703  thisDir.remove(Doxygen::entryDBFileName);
10704  }
10705  if (!Doxygen::objDBFileName.isEmpty())
10706  {
10707  thisDir.remove(Doxygen::objDBFileName);
10708  }
10709  }
10710 }
10711 
10712 static QCString createOutputDirectory(const QCString &baseDirName,
10713  QCString &formatDirName,
10714  const char *defaultDirName)
10715 {
10716  // Note the & on the next line, we modify the formatDirOption!
10717  if (formatDirName.isEmpty())
10718  {
10719  formatDirName = baseDirName + defaultDirName;
10720  }
10721  else if (formatDirName[0]!='/' && (formatDirName.length()==1 || formatDirName[1]!=':'))
10722  {
10723  formatDirName.prepend(baseDirName+'/');
10724  }
10725  QDir formatDir(formatDirName);
10726  if (!formatDir.exists() && !formatDir.mkdir(formatDirName))
10727  {
10728  err("Could not create output directory %s\n", formatDirName.data());
10729  cleanUpDoxygen();
10730  exit(1);
10731  }
10732  return formatDirName;
10733 }
10734 
10735 static QCString getQchFileName()
10736 {
10737  QCString const & qchFile = Config_getString(QCH_FILE);
10738  if (!qchFile.isEmpty())
10739  {
10740  return qchFile;
10741  }
10742 
10743  QCString const & projectName = Config_getString(PROJECT_NAME);
10744  QCString const & versionText = Config_getString(PROJECT_NUMBER);
10745 
10746  return QCString("../qch/")
10747  + (projectName.isEmpty() ? QCString("index") : projectName)
10748  + (versionText.isEmpty() ? QCString("") : QCString("-") + versionText)
10749  + QCString(".qch");
10750 }
10751 
10752 void searchInputFiles()
10753 {
10754  QStrList &exclPatterns = Config_getList(EXCLUDE_PATTERNS);
10755  bool alwaysRecursive = Config_getBool(RECURSIVE);
10756  StringDict excludeNameDict(1009);
10757  excludeNameDict.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10758 
10759  // gather names of all files in the include path
10760  g_s.begin("Searching for include files...\n");
10761  QStrList &includePathList = Config_getList(INCLUDE_PATH);
10762  char *s=includePathList.first();
10763  while (s)
10764  {
10765  QStrList &pl = Config_getList(INCLUDE_FILE_PATTERNS);
10766  if (pl.count()==0)
10767  {
10768  pl = Config_getList(FILE_PATTERNS);
10769  }
10770  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::includeNameDict,0,&pl,
10771  &exclPatterns,0,0,
10772  alwaysRecursive);
10773  s=includePathList.next();
10774  }
10775  g_s.end();
10776 
10777  g_s.begin("Searching for example files...\n");
10778  QStrList &examplePathList = Config_getList(EXAMPLE_PATH);
10779  s=examplePathList.first();
10780  while (s)
10781  {
10782  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::exampleNameDict,0,
10783  &Config_getList(EXAMPLE_PATTERNS),
10784  0,0,0,
10785  (alwaysRecursive || Config_getBool(EXAMPLE_RECURSIVE)));
10786  s=examplePathList.next();
10787  }
10788  g_s.end();
10789 
10790  g_s.begin("Searching for images...\n");
10791  QStrList &imagePathList=Config_getList(IMAGE_PATH);
10792  s=imagePathList.first();
10793  while (s)
10794  {
10795  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::imageNameDict,0,0,
10796  0,0,0,
10797  alwaysRecursive);
10798  s=imagePathList.next();
10799  }
10800  g_s.end();
10801 
10802  g_s.begin("Searching for dot files...\n");
10803  QStrList &dotFileList=Config_getList(DOTFILE_DIRS);
10804  s=dotFileList.first();
10805  while (s)
10806  {
10807  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::dotFileNameDict,0,0,
10808  0,0,0,
10809  alwaysRecursive);
10810  s=dotFileList.next();
10811  }
10812  g_s.end();
10813 
10814  g_s.begin("Searching for msc files...\n");
10815  QStrList &mscFileList=Config_getList(MSCFILE_DIRS);
10816  s=mscFileList.first();
10817  while (s)
10818  {
10819  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::mscFileNameDict,0,0,
10820  0,0,0,
10821  alwaysRecursive);
10822  s=mscFileList.next();
10823  }
10824  g_s.end();
10825 
10826  g_s.begin("Searching for dia files...\n");
10827  QStrList &diaFileList=Config_getList(DIAFILE_DIRS);
10828  s=diaFileList.first();
10829  while (s)
10830  {
10831  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,Doxygen::diaFileNameDict,0,0,
10832  0,0,0,
10833  alwaysRecursive);
10834  s=diaFileList.next();
10835  }
10836  g_s.end();
10837 
10838  g_s.begin("Searching for files to exclude\n");
10839  QStrList &excludeList = Config_getList(EXCLUDE);
10840  s=excludeList.first();
10841  while (s)
10842  {
10843  readFileOrDirectory(s,0,0,0,&Config_getList(FILE_PATTERNS),
10844  0,0,&excludeNameDict,
10845  alwaysRecursive,
10846  FALSE);
10847  s=excludeList.next();
10848  }
10849  g_s.end();
10850 
10851  /**************************************************************************
10852  * Determine Input Files *
10853  **************************************************************************/
10854 
10855  g_s.begin("Searching INPUT for files to process...\n");
10856  QDict<void> *killDict = new QDict<void>(10007);
10857  QStrList &inputList=Config_getList(INPUT);
10858  g_inputFiles.setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10859  s=inputList.first();
10860  while (s)
10861  {
10862  QCString path=s;
10863  uint l = path.length();
10864  if (l>0)
10865  {
10866  // strip trailing slashes
10867  if (path.at(l-1)=='\\' || path.at(l-1)=='/') path=path.left(l-1);
10868 
10869  readFileOrDirectory(
10870  path,
10871  Doxygen::inputNameList,
10872  Doxygen::inputNameDict,
10873  &excludeNameDict,
10874  &Config_getList(FILE_PATTERNS),
10875  &exclPatterns,
10876  &g_inputFiles,0,
10877  alwaysRecursive,
10878  TRUE,
10879  killDict,
10880  &Doxygen::inputPaths);
10881  }
10882  s=inputList.next();
10883  }
10884  delete killDict;
10885  g_s.end();
10886 }

10888 
10889 void parseInput()
10890 {
10891  atexit(exitDoxygen);
10892 
10893 
10894  /**************************************************************************
10895  * Make sure the output directory exists
10896  **************************************************************************/
10897  QCString &outputDirectory = Config_getString(OUTPUT_DIRECTORY);
10898  if (outputDirectory.isEmpty())
10899  {
10900  outputDirectory=QDir::currentDirPath().utf8();
10901  }
10902  else
10903  {
10904  QDir dir(outputDirectory);
10905  if (!dir.exists())
10906  {
10907  dir.setPath(QDir::currentDirPath());
10908  if (!dir.mkdir(outputDirectory))
10909  {
10910  err("tag OUTPUT_DIRECTORY: Output directory `%s' does not "
10911  "exist and cannot be created\n",outputDirectory.data());
10912  cleanUpDoxygen();
10913  exit(1);
10914  }
10915  else
10916  {
10917  msg("Notice: Output directory `%s' does not exist. "
10918  "I have created it for you.\n", outputDirectory.data());
10919  }
10920  dir.cd(outputDirectory);
10921  }
10922  outputDirectory=dir.absPath().utf8();
10923  }
10924 
10925  /**************************************************************************
10926  * Initialize global lists and dictionaries
10927  **************************************************************************/
10928 
10929  Doxygen::symbolStorage = new Store;
10930 
10931  // also scale lookup cache with SYMBOL_CACHE_SIZE
10932  int cacheSize = Config_getInt(LOOKUP_CACHE_SIZE);
10933  if (cacheSize<0) cacheSize=0;
10934  if (cacheSize>9) cacheSize=9;
10935  uint lookupSize = 65536 << cacheSize;
10936  Doxygen::lookupCache = new QCache<LookupInfo>(lookupSize,lookupSize);
10937  Doxygen::lookupCache->setAutoDelete(TRUE);
10938 
10939 #ifdef HAS_SIGNALS
10940  signal(SIGINT, stopDoxygen);
10941 #endif
10942 
10943  uint pid = portable_pid();
10944  Doxygen::objDBFileName.sprintf("doxygen_objdb_%d.tmp",pid);
10945  Doxygen::objDBFileName.prepend(outputDirectory+"/");
10946  Doxygen::entryDBFileName.sprintf("doxygen_entrydb_%d.tmp",pid);
10947  Doxygen::entryDBFileName.prepend(outputDirectory+"/");
10948 
10949  if (Doxygen::symbolStorage->open(Doxygen::objDBFileName)==-1)
10950  {
10951  err("Failed to open temporary file %s\n",Doxygen::objDBFileName.data());
10952  exit(1);
10953  }
10954 
10955 
10956 
10957  /**************************************************************************
10958  * Check/create output directorties *
10959  **************************************************************************/
10960 
10961  QCString htmlOutput;
10962  bool &generateHtml = Config_getBool(GENERATE_HTML);
10963  if (generateHtml || g_useOutputTemplate /* TODO: temp hack */)
10964  htmlOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT),"/html");
10965 
10966  QCString docbookOutput;
10967  bool &generateDocbook = Config_getBool(GENERATE_DOCBOOK);
10968  if (generateDocbook)
10969  docbookOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(DOCBOOK_OUTPUT),"/docbook");
10970 
10971  QCString xmlOutput;
10972  bool &generateXml = Config_getBool(GENERATE_XML);
10973  if (generateXml)
10974  xmlOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(XML_OUTPUT),"/xml");
10975 
10976  QCString latexOutput;
10977  bool &generateLatex = Config_getBool(GENERATE_LATEX);
10978  if (generateLatex)
10979  latexOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(LATEX_OUTPUT),"/latex");
10980 
10981  QCString rtfOutput;
10982  bool &generateRtf = Config_getBool(GENERATE_RTF);
10983  if (generateRtf)
10984  rtfOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(RTF_OUTPUT),"/rtf");
10985 
10986  QCString manOutput;
10987  bool &generateMan = Config_getBool(GENERATE_MAN);
10988  if (generateMan)
10989  manOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,Config_getString(MAN_OUTPUT),"/man");
10990 
10991  //QCString sqlOutput;
10992  //bool &generateSql = Config_getBool(GENERATE_SQLITE3);
10993  //if (generateSql)
10994  // sqlOutput = createOutputDirectory(outputDirectory,"SQLITE3_OUTPUT","/sqlite3");
10995 
10996  if (Config_getBool(HAVE_DOT))
10997  {
10998  QCString curFontPath = Config_getString(DOT_FONTPATH);
10999  if (curFontPath.isEmpty())
11000  {
11001  portable_getenv("DOTFONTPATH");
11002  QCString newFontPath = ".";
11003  if (!curFontPath.isEmpty())
11004  {
11005  newFontPath+=portable_pathListSeparator();
11006  newFontPath+=curFontPath;
11007  }
11008  portable_setenv("DOTFONTPATH",newFontPath);
11009  }
11010  else
11011  {
11012  portable_setenv("DOTFONTPATH",curFontPath);
11013  }
11014  }
11015 
11016 
11017 
11018  /**************************************************************************
11019  * Handle layout file *
11020  **************************************************************************/
11021 
11022  LayoutDocManager::instance().init();
11023  QCString &layoutFileName = Config_getString(LAYOUT_FILE);
11024  bool defaultLayoutUsed = FALSE;
11025  if (layoutFileName.isEmpty())
11026  {
11027  layoutFileName = "DoxygenLayout.xml";
11028  defaultLayoutUsed = TRUE;
11029  }
11030 
11031  QFile layoutFile(layoutFileName);
11032  if (layoutFile.open(IO_ReadOnly))
11033  {
11034  msg("Parsing layout file %s...\n",layoutFileName.data());
11035  QTextStream t(&layoutFile);
11036  t.setEncoding(QTextStream::Latin1);
11037  LayoutDocManager::instance().parse(t,layoutFileName);
11038  }
11039  else if (!defaultLayoutUsed)
11040  {
11041  warn_uncond("failed to open layout file '%s' for reading!\n",layoutFileName.data());
11042  }
11043 
11044  /**************************************************************************
11045  * Read and preprocess input *
11046  **************************************************************************/
11047 
11048  // prevent search in the output directories
11049  QStrList &exclPatterns = Config_getList(EXCLUDE_PATTERNS);
11050  if (generateHtml) exclPatterns.append(htmlOutput);
11051  if (generateDocbook) exclPatterns.append(docbookOutput);
11052  if (generateXml) exclPatterns.append(xmlOutput);
11053  if (generateLatex) exclPatterns.append(latexOutput);
11054  if (generateRtf) exclPatterns.append(rtfOutput);
11055  if (generateMan) exclPatterns.append(manOutput);
11056 
11057  searchInputFiles();
11058 
11059  // Notice: the order of the function calls below is very important!
11060 
11061  if (Config_getBool(GENERATE_HTML))
11062  {
11063  readFormulaRepository();
11064  }
11065 
11066  /**************************************************************************
11067  * Handle Tag Files *
11068  **************************************************************************/
11069 
11070  g_storage = new FileStorage;
11071  g_storage->setName(Doxygen::entryDBFileName);
11072  if (!g_storage->open(IO_WriteOnly))
11073  {
11074  err("Failed to create temporary storage file %s\n",
11075  Doxygen::entryDBFileName.data());
11076  exit(1);
11077  }
11078  Entry *root=new Entry;
11079  EntryNav *rootNav = new EntryNav(0,root);
11080  rootNav->setEntry(root);
11081  msg("Reading and parsing tag files\n");
11082 
11083  QStrList &tagFileList = Config_getList(TAGFILES);
11084  char *s=tagFileList.first();
11085  while (s)
11086  {
11087  readTagFile(root,s);
11088  root->createNavigationIndex(rootNav,g_storage,0);
11089  s=tagFileList.next();
11090  }
11091 
11092  /**************************************************************************
11093  * Parse source files *
11094  **************************************************************************/
11095 
11096  if (Config_getBool(BUILTIN_STL_SUPPORT))
11097  {
11098  addSTLClasses(rootNav);
11099  }
11100 
11101  g_s.begin("Parsing files\n");
11102  parseFiles(root,rootNav);
11103  g_storage->close();
11104  g_s.end();
11105 
11106  // we are done with input scanning now, so free up the buffers used by flex
11107  // (can be around 4MB)
11108  preFreeScanner();
11109  scanFreeScanner();
11110  pyscanFreeScanner();
11111 
11112  if (!g_storage->open(IO_ReadOnly))
11113  {
11114  err("Failed to open temporary storage file %s for reading",
11115  Doxygen::entryDBFileName.data());
11116  exit(1);
11117  }
11118 
11119  /**************************************************************************
11120  * Gather information *
11121  **************************************************************************/
11122 
11123  g_s.begin("Building group list...\n");
11124  buildGroupList(rootNav);
11125  organizeSubGroups(rootNav);
11126  g_s.end();
11127 
11128  g_s.begin("Building directory list...\n");
11129  buildDirectories();
11130  findDirDocumentation(rootNav);
11131  g_s.end();
11132 
11133  g_s.begin("Building namespace list...\n");
11134  buildNamespaceList(rootNav);
11135  findUsingDirectives(rootNav);
11136  g_s.end();
11137 
11138  g_s.begin("Building file list...\n");
11139  buildFileList(rootNav);
11140  g_s.end();
11141  //generateFileTree();
11142 
11143  g_s.begin("Building class list...\n");
11144  buildClassList(rootNav);
11145  g_s.end();
11146 
11147  g_s.begin("Associating documentation with classes...\n");
11148  buildClassDocList(rootNav);
11149 
11150  // build list of using declarations here (global list)
11151  buildListOfUsingDecls(rootNav);
11152  g_s.end();
11153 
11154  g_s.begin("Computing nesting relations for classes...\n");
11155  resolveClassNestingRelations();
11156  g_s.end();
11157  // 1.8.2-20121111: no longer add nested classes to the group as well
11158  //distributeClassGroupRelations();
11159 
11160  // calling buildClassList may result in cached relations that
11161  // become invalid after resolveClassNestingRelations(), that's why
11162  // we need to clear the cache here
11163  Doxygen::lookupCache->clear();
11164  // we don't need the list of using declaration anymore
11165  g_usingDeclarations.clear();
11166

11168  buildExampleList(rootNav);
11169  g_s.end();
11170 
11171  g_s.begin("Searching for enumerations...\n");
11172  findEnums(rootNav);
11173  g_s.end();
11174 
11175  // Since buildVarList calls isVarWithConstructor
11176  // and this calls getResolvedClass we need to process
11177  // typedefs first so the relations between classes via typedefs
11178  // are properly resolved. See bug 536385 for an example.
11179  g_s.begin("Searching for documented typedefs...\n");
11180  buildTypedefList(rootNav);
11181  g_s.end();

11184  findUsingDeclImports(rootNav);
11185  // this should be after buildTypedefList in order to properly import
11186  // used typedefs
11187  findUsingDeclarations(rootNav);
11188  g_s.end();

11191  findIncludedUsingDirectives();
11192  g_s.end();
11193 
11194  g_s.begin("Searching for documented variables...\n");
11195  buildVarList(rootNav);
11196  g_s.end();
11197

11199  buildInterfaceAndServiceList(rootNav); // UNO IDL
11200 
11201  g_s.begin("Building member list...\n"); // using class info only !
11202  buildFunctionList(rootNav);
11203  g_s.end();
11204 
11205  g_s.begin("Searching for friends...\n");
11206  findFriends();
11207  g_s.end();
11208 
11209  g_s.begin("Searching for documented defines...\n");
11210  findDefineDocumentation(rootNav);
11211  g_s.end();

11216  g_s.end();
11217

11220  g_s.end();

11227  }

11247  g_s.end();

11252

11258  // as this introduces new members see bug 722654

11279  g_s.end();

11284  Doxygen::hiddenClasses->sort();
11285  Doxygen::classSDict->sort();

11299  g_s.end();

11302  mergeCategories();

11304  g_s.end();

11419 
11420  // add HTML indexers that are enabled
11421  bool generateHtmlHelp = Config_getBool(GENERATE_HTMLHELP);
11422  bool generateEclipseHelp = Config_getBool(GENERATE_ECLIPSEHELP);
11423  bool generateQhp = Config_getBool(GENERATE_QHP);
11424  bool generateTreeView = Config_getBool(GENERATE_TREEVIEW);
11425  bool generateDocSet = Config_getBool(GENERATE_DOCSET);
11426  if (generateEclipseHelp) Doxygen::indexList->addIndex(new EclipseHelp);
11427  if (generateHtmlHelp) Doxygen::indexList->addIndex(new HtmlHelp);
11428  if (generateQhp) Doxygen::indexList->addIndex(new Qhp);

11430  if (generateDocSet) Doxygen::indexList->addIndex(new DocSets);
11431  Doxygen::indexList->initialize();

11433  }

11435  {

11437  LatexGenerator::init();
11438  }

11440  {
11441  g_outputList->add(new ManGenerator);
11442  ManGenerator::init();
11443  }
11444  if (generateRtf)
11445  {
11446  g_outputList->add(new RTFGenerator);
11447  RTFGenerator::init();

11450  {

11452  QCString htmldir = Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT);
11453  if (!Htags::execute(htmldir))
11454  err("USE_HTAGS is YES but htags(1) failed. \n");
11455  if (!Htags::loadFilemap(htmldir))
11456  err("htags(1) ended normally but failed to load the filemap. \n");
11457  }
11458

11460  * Generate documentation *
11461  **************************************************************************/
11462 
11463  if (generateHtml) writeDoxFont(Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT));
11464  if (generateLatex) writeDoxFont(Config_getString(LATEX_OUTPUT));
11465  if (generateRtf) writeDoxFont(Config_getString(RTF_OUTPUT));
11466

11468  //printf("writing style info\n");
11469  g_outputList->writeStyleInfo(0); // write first part
11470  g_s.end();
11471

11473  static bool serverBasedSearch = Config_getBool(SERVER_BASED_SEARCH);

11477  {
11478  createJavascriptSearchIndex();
11479  }
11480 
11481  // generate search indices (need to do this before writing other HTML
11482  // pages as these contain a drop down menu with options depending on
11483  // what categories we find in this function.

11485  {
11486  QCString searchDirName = Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT)+"/search";
11487  QDir searchDir(searchDirName);

11491  searchDirName.data(),QDir::currentDirPath().data());

11494  HtmlGenerator::writeSearchData(searchDirName);
11495  if (!serverBasedSearch) // client side search index
11496  {
11497  writeJavascriptSearchIndex();
11498  }
11499  }
11500  g_s.end();
11501 
11502  g_s.begin("Generating example documentation...\n");
11503  generateExampleDocs();
11504  g_s.end();

11507  {

11510  g_s.end();
11511  }

11537  g_s.end();
11538  }

11543

11545  && !Config_getBool(USE_MATHJAX))

11692  {
11693  err("failed to run html help compiler on index.hhp\n");
11694  }

11699  if ( generateHtml &&

11702  {

11705  QCString const qchFileName = getQchFileName();
11706

11708  QString const oldDir = QDir::currentDirPath();
11709  QDir::setCurrent(Config_getString(HTML_OUTPUT));
11710  portable_sysTimerStart();

11712  {
11713  err("failed to run qhelpgenerator on index.qhp\n");
11714  }
11715  portable_sysTimerStop();
11716  QDir::setCurrent(oldDir);
11717  g_s.end();
11718  }
11719 
11720  int cacheParam;
11721  msg("lookup cache used %d/%d hits=%d misses=%d\n",
11722  Doxygen::lookupCache->count(),
11723  Doxygen::lookupCache->size(),
11724  Doxygen::lookupCache->hits(),
11725  Doxygen::lookupCache->misses());
11726  cacheParam = computeIdealCacheParam(Doxygen::lookupCache->misses()*2/3); // part of the cache is flushed, hence the 2/3 correction factor
11727  if (cacheParam>Config_getInt(LOOKUP_CACHE_SIZE))
11728  {
11729  msg("Note: based on cache misses the ideal setting for LOOKUP_CACHE_SIZE is %d at the cost of higher memory usage.\n",cacheParam);
11730  }
11731 
11732  if (Debug::isFlagSet(Debug::Time))
11733  {
11734  msg("Total elapsed time: %.3f seconds\n(of which %.3f seconds waiting for external tools to finish)\n",
11735  ((double)Doxygen::runningTime.elapsed())/1000.0,
11736  portable_getSysElapsedTime()
11737  );
11738  g_s.print();
11739  }
11740  else
11741  {
11742  msg("finished...\n");
11743  }
11744 
11745 
11746  /**************************************************************************
11747  * Start cleaning up *
11748  **************************************************************************/
11749 
11750  cleanUpDoxygen();
11751 
11752  finializeSearchIndexer();
11753  Doxygen::symbolStorage->close();
11754  QDir thisDir;
11755  thisDir.remove(Doxygen::objDBFileName);
11756  Config::deinit();
11757  QTextCodec::deleteAllCodecs();
11758  delete Doxygen::symbolMap;
11759  delete Doxygen::clangUsrMap;
11760  delete Doxygen::symbolStorage;
11761  g_successfulRun=TRUE;
11762 }
